title: italian beef
directions: Place meat in crock-pot and cover with other ingredients. Cook on low overnight or 8 to 10 hours.

title: eggs fertata
directions: Brown sausage.
Add all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° with a cover. Then bake 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with graham crackers after spraying pan with Pam. Melt butter with brown sugar in saucepan. Bring to full boil and boil 1 minute. Add walnuts. Spoon over graham crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes ONLY.

title: shrimp etouffee for 24 people
directions: Chop onions, celery, bell peppers, garlic and green onions. Saute in butter.
Squeeze lemons and add to mixture.
Place Ro-Tel tomatoes in food processor and whip.
Add tomatoes, mushroom soup and mushrooms to mixture.
Add at least 4 cups water.

title: crab quiche
directions: Whip the first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Makes enough for a 9-inch shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Combine in large bowl.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend until smooth, approximately 30 seconds.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except butter. Pour into greased casserole. Melt butter and drizzle on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: golden cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower in 1 cup water.
Drain; reserving liquid. Reserve 1 cup cauliflower.
In blender, blend remaining cauliflower and reserved liquid.
Cook onion in butter until tender; stir in flour.
Gradually add 1 cup water and bouillon, stirring until well blended and thickened.
Stir in all cauliflower and cheese; cook until cheese melts.
Add milk and nutmeg and heat through.
Garnish with parsley and paprika.

title: no fail pie crust(makes 4 shells)
directions: Cut shortening into flour until it resembles small crumbs.
Add salt and sugar.
Add vinegar and then cold water (just enough to make it stick together and easy to work with).

title: cheese-apple starlets cookies
directions: Combine cheese, flour and salt.
Cut shortening into mixture until it resembles coarse meal.
Add milk and mix.

title: apricot gelatin
directions: Mix Jell-O in hot water and hot pear juice until dissolved. Pour over softened cream cheese; beat with mixer until creamed. Stick in freezer until it starts to jell (30 minutes or so). After jelled, add chopped pears and Mandarin oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: beef taco dip
directions: Add onion to ground beef while browning; drain meat very well. Add remaining ingredients, except taco chips, to beef mixture; simmer until cheese melts.
Serve with taco chips.

title: cran-raspberry mold
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and cranberry sauce, stirring until cranberry sauce melts.
Chill in refrigerator.
Pour half of gelatin mixture into a 6 1/2-cup mold.
Chill until almost firm.
Let the remaining gelatin stand at room temperature.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs with mixer until foamy.
Add sugar, flour and cornstarch.
Slowly add milk.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat; add salt, vanilla, oleo and coconut.
Return to heat; cook until coconut, salt and vanilla are hot and mixed well with pie filling.
Pour in 9 or 9 5/8-inch baked pie crust.
Top with meringue.
Bake until golden brown.

title: ham and cheese calzones
directions: Unroll one pizza crust, stretching gently to make a 14 x 11-inch rectangle.
Spread half of the Ricotta on half of the dough lengthwise, to within 1 inch of the edges.
Sprinkle with half of the pepperoni, ham and Mozzarella.
Fold unfilled side of dough over filled half and press edges together firmly to seal.
Transfer to a greased baking sheet.
Repeat with other crust and ingredients.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer the first 6 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together; spread over the top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bacon bits.

title: cooked dressing for slaw
directions: Mix ingredients and cook until thick.
Cool and pour over grated cabbage.
Wonderful with pinto beans.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan with margarine. Pour peaches and juice into pan. Sprinkle cake mix over peaches and pat down so the surface is smooth. Cover the top with margarine, bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix together the first 8 ingredients and pour into the pie shell.
Bake at 325° until golden brown (approximately 20 minutes).

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and cut in pieces the size of thumb.
Put into 1 1/2 quarts salted boiling water; cook until tender.
Add finely chopped onion, cracker crumbs and butter while very hot; mix well. Beat up eggs and add milk; turn into eggplant mixture.
Add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz (optional).
Bake in casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add other ingredients except nuts.
Mix well. Add nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pineapple-lime delight salad
directions: Spread lime jello over pineapple.
Mix Cool Whip and sour cream together; pour over fruit and jello.
Add small marshmallows.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter fudge rolls
directions: Dough:
In a mixing bowl, cut margarine or butter into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in sour cream until mixture forms a ball.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Place chicken in ungreased baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients; pour over chicken. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour. Line broiler pan with foil. Place chicken on rack in broiler pan. Brush chicken with remaining sauce. Cook in 375° oven until done, about 60 to 70 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix grated cheese, 1 stick melted butter, soup, water, onion and sour cream together and pour over hash browns in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Spread crumbs over top and then pour 1/2 stick butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lo-cal fruit salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine Cool Whip and both envelopes of Jell-O.
Mix well. Add pineapple and oranges (mix thoroughly). Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: christmas stollen
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup of warm water.
Add sugar, salt, butter, eggs and yolk, and 1 3/4 cups of flour.
Beat 10 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer or by hand.
Scrape bowl frequently.
Stir in other 1 3/4 cups flour, and rest of ingredients.
Cover, let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Beat 25 strokes.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Add celery and onions (makes good stock).
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and stir to a smooth paste.
Add chicken stock and milk gradually.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Turn into baking dish.
Add sliced, boiled eggs.
While still hot, cover with biscuits made very light and cut into desired shapes.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in hot oven at 375° to 400°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan bread, cheese, sausage, mushrooms, bell pepper; mix and pour over layered ingredients, half and half, eggs, salt, Worcestershire sauce, red pepper sauce, Beau Monde. Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Melt butter; add granulated sugar and graham cracker crumbs, place in the bottom of a baking dish.
Whip Dream Whip; add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Place on top of the graham cracker crumb layer.
Top with can of cherry pie filling.

title: rosolli(herring salad)
directions: Soak the herring in cold water for 24 hours, then skin and fillet.
Combine the whipped cream, beet juice, sugar and vinegar. Chill.
Cut the herring into cubes and combine with the remaining ingredients, with the exception of the parsley.
Mix well.
Fold in the whipped cream dressing.
Chill.
Garnish with the parsley and serve.

title: texas casserole
directions: Brown meat, chopped onion and bell pepper in skillet using no oil.
Drain.
Add seasoning and tomatoes.
In another pot, boil rice and carrots 10 minutes.
Combine with meat mixture and bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Grate cheese on top, if desired.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Remove pulp, reserving 1/4-inch shells.
Chop pulp.
Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons olive oil in skillet.
Stir in chopped zucchini. Saute 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, capers, olives and seasonings. Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in bread crumbs and half the cheese.
Spoon into shells.
Top with remaining cheese.
Drizzle with 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana muffins
directions: Optional:
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring or black walnut flavoring.

title: boiled chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo in boiler; bring to a boil. Boil 2 minutes.
Set off stove; add remaining ingredients.
Mix and drop on wax paper.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients well.
Gradually add enough milk to make a paste.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Add remainder of milk. Cook slowly, stirring constantly to prevent sticking.
When thickened, remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue and brown.

title: easy rice and vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onions and butter until done.
Pour 2 cups Minute rice in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour the sauteed onions in over the rice.
Cover with California Blend.
Mix mushroom soup and water. Pour over vegetables.
Spoon Cheez Whiz over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine all, except chips, and turn into baking dish.
Top with chips.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add water to reserved pineapple juice to make 2 cups.
Add Jell-O.
Refrigerate.
Chop 1 pound of cranberries.
Pour 2 cups of sugar over and let stand until Jell-O is slightly jelled.
Fold cranberries, celery and nuts into jelled mixture.
Fold in gently. Chill until firmly set.

title: four layer crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Blend the next 3 ingredients together for layer two.
Pour on top of crust. Blend the next 3 ingredients for layer three and spread.
Top with Cool Whip and pecans for layer four.

title: key lime pie
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve Jell-O in 1/4 cup boiling water; whip in yogurt.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread in graham cracker crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Only 148 calories in pie.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook ground beef.
Mix seasoning mix while cooking meat and then drain.
On bottom of pan, spread ground beef, then layer overlapping tortillas.
Pour 1 can Ranch beans and 1 can cream of chicken soup (dab it on the beans).
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes; add cheese on top and repeat all ingredients again; cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed italian shells
directions: In large pot, cook manicotti noodles, a few at a time, in salted water.
Lift out with a slotted spoon so as not to break. Place in large bowl with cold water.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out pie dough and cut into 4 equal pieces.
Peel and core apples and sprinkle them with lemon.
Place 1 apple in center of each pieces of dough. Combine sugar replacement and cinnamon in a bowl, sprinkling evenly into cavity of apples.
Top each apple with 1 teaspoon (5 ml) margarine.
Bring opposite ends of dough up over apple.
Moisten slightly with water; seal securely.
Brush with beaten egg white and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 425°F (220°C) for 35 to 45 minutes or until pastry is golden brown.
Yield: 4 dumplings.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine soy sauce, mustard, ginger and brown sugar.
Marinate chicken overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Pour out marinade and bake 10 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Cook sugar and water together until clear.
Mix lemonade, pineapple juice, strawberries and almond extract together along with sugar and water. Freeze.
Do this 3 or 4 days before party. Add sherbet 2 hours before party along with the ginger ale when base is put into punch bowl.
Makes sort of a slush or can thin to likeness.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Put chicken in a 4-quart pan and add just enough water to cover chicken.
Boil until chicken is tender.
Reserve stock and 1 cup of chopped chicken for later use.

title: creamed tuna and peas
directions: Heat a large skillet and add the butter.
When the butter is melted, stir in the flour.
Add the peas and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in tuna.
Heat through and serve over toast or pasta.

title: chicken hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut chicken into bite sized pieces.
Dip chicken in melted butter and then in crumb mixture.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes on a foil lined cookie sheet.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Boil rapidly the sugar and milk for 6 minutes.
Pour over chocolate chips, marshmallows, butter
and nuts.
Beat until firm. Pour into greased baking sheet.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Quarter biscuits and roll each quarter in a mixture of 1/2 c. sugar and 1/2 tsp. cinnamon. Pile in a greased and floured 9 x 9 pan. Melt stick of butter in saucepan. Add 3/4 c. sugar and 3/4 tsp. cinnamon. Heat until sugar melts. Pour over biscuits. Bake for 20-25 minutes. Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes. Invert on a cake plate. Pull pieces apart with fingers.

title: chili(good)
directions: Brown beef, onions and green pepper.
Put other ingredients in pot and mix.
Add meat mixture.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add salt and cinnamon.
Stir in carrots, raisins, nuts, coconut and apples.
In other bowl, whisk eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture and stir just until combined.
Spoon into well-greased and floured muffin tins, filling to top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Let cool in tins for 5 minutes, then put on rack to cool.
Makes 30.

title: judy's cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread and add remaining ingredients.
Stir all until mixed thoroughly.
Chill and serve.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In 2-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions.
Top with Miracle Whip, sealing to edge of bowl and cover.
Chill several hours or overnight. Garnish with bacon and cheese, if desired.

title: copper pennies
directions: Combine all ingredients except vegetables.
Pour over carrots, onions and bell pepper.
Marinate for 12 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake in an ungreased casserole dish at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: lime jello dessert
directions: Mix the jello with the hot water.
Add the Karo syrup and lemon juice.
Mix and place in refrigerator until it begins to thicken.
Have the evaporated milk chilled.
Place in cold bowl and beat until thick.
Fold into mixture.
Place in pan; sprinkle crushed Nabiscos over top.

title: heiser kraut salat(hot cabbage salad)
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add water, sugar, vinegar and salt and pepper to taste.
When mixture in pan comes to a boil, add cabbage. Cover tightly and turn down heat.
Cook until cabbage is tender.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar together in a saucepan.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Mix well by hand.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
This is all mixed by hand.
Leave in saucepan and refrigerate for at least 5 hours or overnight and for several days.
Heat oven at 350°.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough into sugar.
Roll into balls.
Place 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Put all ingredients together, except for chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix in bowl and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chocolate chips on top of batter.
Nutmeats may be added with chocolate chips.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Scrap centers from Oreos.
Crush Oreos in a food processor; set aside.
Mix pudding and milk; set aside.
Cream or mix sugar, cream cheese and margarine, fold into pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place 1/2 crushed cookies on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish, spread mixture over cookies, then spread the other 1/2 of cookies on top.

title: rice chili
directions: Brown ground meat with onion in skillet. Drain.
Add canned tomatoes and chili powder.
Simmer for approximately 10 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.

title: cinnamon crisp tortillas
directions: Preheat broiler; arrange tortillas on nonstick baking sheet and brush each tortilla with 1/4 of margarine and sprinkle 1/4 of cinnamon.
Broil until bubbly.
Combine remaining cinnamon with the sugar.
Turn tortilla over; brush with the remaining margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Broil until caramelizes, about 1 minute.
Weight Watcher = 1/2 fat; 1 bread; .5 calories.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and margarine with sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Stir in flavoring and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: fried turkey
directions: Wash and drain turkey.
Punch small holes in turkey and insert Cajun seasoning all through the turkey and salt and pepper to taste.
Let turkey sit in refrigerator overnight.
Fry in deep pot, cook turkey 3 1/2 minutes per pound; should take about 35 or 40 minutes according to size.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients. Shape into balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown. Cook the Heinz chili sauce and grape jelly until jelly melts.
Add meatballs and simmer 10 minutes.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Wash fresh spinach thoroughly.
Add salt and cook until tender.
Do not add water.
Chop fresh spinach very fine.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Blend in a mixture of flour, pepper and nutmeg.
Heat until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat; add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil; cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Blend spinach into sauce and serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crabmeat thermidor
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender. Stir into cream sauce the onion, green pepper and cheese.
Heat slowly but do not boil. Remove from heat and add crabmeat and lemon juice. Garnish with parsley and paprika.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil, stirring constantly, then add lemon juice.
Fill 7-quarts with sliced apples (Jonathans). Pour hot syrup over apples and seal.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: onion pepper steak
directions: Rub steaks with pepper. Melt butter in a skillet and sear steaks on both sides. Add garlic and onions and saute about 5 minutes. Combine beef broth, Worcestershire sauce and tomatoes. Pour over steaks and simmer for approximately 25 minutes or to desired doneness. Serve over rice with sauce leftover in pan.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Use a cookie sheet and line with aluminum foil.
Leave overhang to cover potatoes completely.
Slice potatoes and chop onions, add mushrooms, pour oil over and slice stick butter and leave on top.
Season to taste with seasonings above.
While grilling out simply place pan on rack and bake until tender. Garnish with bacon bits, sour cream, chives and cheese. MMMMM Good.

title: chili rellenos squares
directions: Place half of the cheeses in a greased 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with chilies and remaining cheeses. In a bowl, beat the eggs. Add the milk and flour; pour over cheeses. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until set. Cut into small squares. Serve warm. Yield: 16 servings.

title: crescent cordon bleu
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In bowl, combine chicken, ham, mushrooms and cheese.
Separate dough into 8 rectangles; press perforations to seal.
Spoon rounded 1/2 cup mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to center; twist slightly.
Seal edges.
Place on cookie sheet; brush with egg.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 24 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cut beef into small cubes and place in baking dish.
Add the soups, mixing together before pouring over beef.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 1 or 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Break cake into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into angel food cake pan and freeze.
Unmold by quickly dipping pan in hot water.
Turn out and slice.
This may be kept frozen for weeks.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Pour into 2 baked pie crusts.
Mix 1 can blueberry pie filling with small can crushed pineapple, drained.
Mix well and spoon over mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: cheese kolacky
directions: Cream together margarine and cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Sift 2 cups flour, salt and mix into margarine and cheese mixture. Chill overnight.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut into 2-inch or 3-inch squares
and place a dab of some dried fruit and preserves mixed with raisins or anything else you may like on each square.
Fold over and seal edges.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes on cookie sheet at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in dish.
Mix sour cream and corn.
Pour into dish with butter.
Do not mix.
Sprinkle Jiffy mix over top evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cornbread mixture is golden brown and set.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt; boil 5 minutes.
Add marshmallows, chips, nuts and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour in buttered 9-inch square pan and cool.

title: cheese cake
directions: In small pan, soften gelatin in orange and pineapple juice. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Place cottage cheese and sweetener in blender.
Blend until smoother.
Add juice.
Blend until smooth.
Add juice.
Blend.
Pour into small round cake pan. Refrigerate until firm.
This equals two fruits and a lunch protein.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: In a buttered casserole dish, place the pineapple first.
Mix sugar and flour; pour over pineapple.
Pour the juice on top of this and then add the cheese.
Top with 1 stack of crushed Ritz crackers and 1 stick margarine.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chili quiche appetizer
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread chilies and cheese in pan. Beat remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: mexican meat dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage together.
Drain.
Add mushroom soup and cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Add chili seasoning. Serve warm with chips.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together (make it light); add eggs one at a time and add vanilla.
Then add flour and 7-Up gradually and alternately.
Grease tube pan.
Dust with 10x sugar.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients in the upper part of double boiler.
Add the milk slowly to dry ingredients and place over boiling water. Stir constantly to prevent lumping.
Next, add well beaten eggs. Cook to the consistency of thick cream.
Add butter and vinegar and let cool.

title: sis smith's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly in a bowl.
Stir in sugar, syrup, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in oven 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: sponge cake(my mother's recipe, 1915)
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick; gradually add sugar and beat two minutes.
Add cold water.
Sift together flour, cornstarch, salt and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.
Add lemon extract.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into flour mixture.
Bake in an angel cake pan 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Be sure to grease and flour the pan well.

title: shrimp and spinach pasta
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil until transparent.
Add spinach, shrimp, oregano, pepper flakes, basil and chicken broth. Simmer until shrimp turn pink.
Add linguini; stir and heat through, about 1 minute.
To serve, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: meat loaf
directions: Can use cracker in place of bread crumbs.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pack into a baking dish.
Omit the salt if using crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan or glass dish.
Line bottom of pan with graham crackers.
Mix	pudding with milk; beat 2 or 3 minutes at medium
speed.
Fold
Cool Whip into pudding.
Pour half of mixture
over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and pour remaining mixture.	Add
a	top layer of crackers and refrigerate for two hours before adding the frosting.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cut 1 package flour tortillas in 1/4 sections and put layers of tortillas, sauce, cheese and onion until casserole is full. Top with cheese. Bake about 30 minutes until thick at 350°.

title: pecan logs
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Shape into rolls and chill. Melt caramels with 3 tablespoons water.
Pour over chilled logs. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato until soft.
Pour off water and mash potato.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
It is very stiff.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Spread peanut butter on dough.
Roll up and place in refrigerator.
Slice as needed.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; pour into ovenproof dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine the sugars and water in saucepan.
Bring to boiling point.
Boil 5 minutes.
Gradually stir in coffee, use a wire whisk.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour mixture into jug.
Add vodka and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover and let stand for 2 weeks.

title: city chicken
directions: You will also need 12 to 15 city chicken wooden skewers/sticks (ask the butcher at your local supermarket for these).

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in a 9 or 10-inch glass pie dish.
Spread chili on top of cheese.
Sprinkle chopped scallions on top of chili, then add the Cheddar cheese on top of scallions.
Microwave 5 minutes until cheese is bubbly.
Or heat in oven at 350°, approximately 20 to 25 minutes, or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with chips on the side.

title: one banana drink delight
directions: Place chopped banana into small bowl.
Stir in vanilla, honey, skimmed milk, brown sugar and Coffee-mate.
Beat for one minute with electric mixer or blender.
Put into cup with ice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Put into greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: mint julep
directions: In a tall, heavy glass, muddle a few mint leaves with sugar. (To muddle, use muddler or long handle teaspoon to crush and bruise mint leaves against grains of sugar.)
If preparing many drinks, refrigerate them now.
Just before serving, fill glass with ice. Add bourbon to taste and fill the rest of the glass with water. Pass the lemon peel around the glass rim; then put in glass.
Stir and serve with spring of mint.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Place the sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add the remaining ingredients, starting with peanut butter and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and allow to cool and take form.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Pare and slice apples; set aside.
Mix together 5 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Beat together all remaining ingredients until smooth and thick.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan. Put a layer of batter, then a layer of apples, then sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Repeat two times.
Top with sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: western scramble(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Beat eggs and milk with fork.
In small skillet, cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Pour in egg mixture.
Cook over low heat.
Lift eggs gently now and then until eggs are set but still moist.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in 1/2-inch slices.
Steam until tender.
Drain. Grate carrots and chop onion.
Add to squash.
Add butter and soup.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan and pat to form a crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar until blended.
Spread over cooled pretzel crust. Dissolve jello in water, add frozen strawberries and mix.
Gel until slightly thickened and pour over layers.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: crumbly apple pie
directions: Slice apples into 9-inch Pyrex pie pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
With pastry blender, crumble flour, brown sugar and margarine.
Press lightly on apples.
Bake until brown and apples are tender at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and set aside. Cook broccoli.
Drain well.
Cook celery and onion in butter until tender, not browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in water until tender.
Place squash in casserole dish.
Top with onion, beaten eggs, melted butter and cheese. Bake at 350° until done, about 25 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter; press crumbs and butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan or loaf pan to form crust.
Mix together eggs, 1 stick butter and powdered sugar; beat 10 minutes.
Spread over crumbs.
Cover with pineapple, then sliced bananas and then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Gradually add milk to cream cheese; blend until smooth.
Add whipped cream and sugar.
Beat mixture for two minutes.
Place pudding in large mixing bowl, gradually add cream cheese mixture to pudding.
Beat until blended; pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Make an indentation in the center of mix for the fruit filling.
Add fruit filling and chill before serving.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in pineapple juice.
Mix ginger ale to this. Place sherbet in punch bowl or large pitcher.
Pour juice-ginger ale over.
Stir slightly and use ladle to dip and serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9-inch square pan.

title: spiced russian tea
directions: Mix together and store tightly in covered container.
To serve, mix 1 1/2 tablespoons mix, 1 cup hot water and 2/3 ounces rum (optional).

title: banana nut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream margarine, shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Add dry ingredients slowly.
Fold in bananas and nuts.
Pour into large tube cake pan, greased and floured, and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: In a bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water (105° to 115°).
Blend in the flour.
Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured board and knead it until it is smooth.
Break off small pieces of dough; roll them into ropes.
Twist the ropes into the traditional pretzel shape.
Arrange the pretzels on cookie sheets, lined with greased paper.
Brush them with beaten egg and sprinkle them generously with salt.

title: chicken wings chinese
directions: Soak wings in cold water with garlic powder for 1 hour.
Lay on paper towels to get water out.
Pat dry, then add to marinade. Marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta following package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Mix vegetables with pasta.
Add salad dressing.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter together.
Add sugar and continue to beat.
Add eggs, one at a time.

title: emily's terrific toffee bars
directions: Mix well the butter, sugar, brown sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Add and blend well the flour and oats.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Take out of oven and immediately place chocolate chips on top of bars.
Wait 5 minutes and spread chips to completely cover bars.
Add nuts.
Cool and serve.

title: moms fudge
directions: Melt in a double boiler butter, marshmallows; bring to slow boil, 6 minutes.
Add sugar and milk in mixing bowl.
Put chocolate chips and nuts; add hot mixture to chips and nuts.
Beat; pour in a greased pan.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat.
Add firmly packed brown sugar; mix well.
Cool slightly.
Add egg and vanilla; blend.
Add flour, a small amount at a time, mixing well.
Spread in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 12 layer chocolate cake(jewel howell's)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add one egg at a time. Add flour and milk, alternately, beginning and ending with flour. Stir at slow speed.
Put 4 tablespoons (1/4 cup) batter into a Pam sprayed cake pan. Bake only long enough to dry at 350°.
Do not brown. (Or use wax paper in pans.)

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Slightly beat eggs with sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
It will be thick.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 50 or 60 minutes.

title: wontons
directions: Cook
beef
until brown; drain well.
Add onion and 1/4 cup sweet
and	sour
sauce.
To
fill wontons, position each wonton skins with 1 point toward you.
Spoon rounded teaspoon of
beef mixture
just
off	center of skin toward you.
Fold bottom
point of skin over filling.
Tuck point under filling. Roll to cover filling, leaving 1-inch unrolled at top of skin. Moisten right corner of skin with water.	Grasp right and left corners;
lap right
corner over left corner.
Press to seal. Fry wontons,
a few at a time, in deep hot oil (365°) for 2 to 3
minutes
or until golden.
Drain on paper toweling.
Cool. Store
in
airtight container and refrigerate or freeze for up to 1
month.
Reheat: Preheat to 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until warm.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Use 3 heaping teaspoonfuls to each cup boiling water.
Store in airtight container.

title: triple berry wake-up breakfast
directions: Spread some cream cheese on two pieces of bread.
Top with sliced berries, making a complete blanket over the cheese.
Top each with the remaining bread.
In a bowl, beat egg and milk.
In a frying pan or griddle, melt butter over medium-high.
Dip the sandwich in the egg mixture and fry until golden on both sides. Top with strawberry syrup or confectioners sugar and serve immediately.
Yields 2 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, soda and salt. Combine shortening, sugar, vanilla and water.
Beat until creamy.
Beat the eggs.
Add flour mixture and mix well. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Leave on cookie sheet 1 minute.
Remove and place on foil to cool.

title: italian nut balls
directions: Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip in egg white and roll in chopped nuts.
Indent with finger.
Fill dent with preserve of your choice.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: wednesday's frosty
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender, using the on/off switch at high speed until smooth with a milkshake consistency.
Serve promptly.
This makes a generous drink.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Mix together and serve with nacho or tortilla chips.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Brown onion and bacon.

title: zemakove placky(potato pancakes)
directions: Add salt to potatoes; add milk, egg, baking powder and flour to make a medium batter.
Drop by spoonfuls on a lightly oiled skillet or griddle.
Brown on one side, turn over and brown on the other side.
Serve hot with butter and jelly or syrup.
Or eat along with a regular meal.
Yields 2 servings.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Melt margarine and pour over stuffing. Mix well. Set aside. Mix first 5 ingredients well. Line bottom of 9 x 13 casserole dish with 1/2 of chicken mixture. Cover with 1/2 stuffing mix. Repeat, ending with stuffing mix. Pour chicken broth over top. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 10 ingredients and mix well.
In a separate bowl, combine honey and water.
Fold dry ingredients into wet ones and mix well.
Do not overbeat or mix. Pour into nonstick 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except sesame seed.
Roll into a ball or log.
Toast sesame seed; cool.
Roll ball in seed.
Serve with crackers.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix together flour and 2/3 cup sugar.
Add to scalded milk. Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Beat egg yolks and add small amount of thickened mixture.
Mix and return to pan.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes more.
Add butter and 1/2 cup coconut.
While this is cooking, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar at a time until 6 tablespoons have been added.

title: christmas holly
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows over low heat.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla and food coloring. Mix well.
Add the corn flakes. Stir until covered. Drop two spoonfuls onto wax paper and put 3 red candies on top of each holly.

title: squash patties
directions: Add enough milk to hold it together. Drop by spoonful into well-greased frying pan.

title: sue's fudge
directions: Mix
sugar,
margarine, marshmallows and milk together, cooking on medium heat.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add
morsels.
Stir
in
nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and cool before cutting.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mash enough berries to make 1 cup pulp.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Add water.
Stir and add pulp.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and translucent, about 10 minutes. Stir in butter and cool.
Place remaining uncooked berries in bottom of cooled pie shell.
Cover with cooked mixture. Refrigerate at least 2 hours and serve with whipped cream.
(If you use frozen berries, thaw and drain, then use juice instead of water.)

title: angel cake
directions: Sift flour with confectioners sugar 3 times.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar, salt, vanilla and almond extract until stiff enough to hold up in soft peaks, but still moist and glossy.
Beat in the granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, continuing to beat until meringue holds stiff peaks.
Sift about 1/4 of flour mixture over whites; fold in.
Fold in remaining flour by fourths. Bake in an ungreased 10-inch tube pan in moderate oven (375°) about 30 minutes or until done.
Invert pan, cool.

title: hush puppies
directions: Adjust milk to be able to drop from spoon to form a ball. Drop into deep, hot oil.
They will turn over when brown on one side.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving size pieces and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put under broiler flame until brown (about 15 minutes, turning once.)
Mix other ingredients in crock-pot (bouillon, brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce).
Put ribs in and cook 6 to 8 hours.
Turn control to high and add onion.
Dissolve cornstarch in small amount of water and stir into pot.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Stir in oranges or pineapple and green pepper.
Cover and cook 5 minutes. Serve over rice and/or Chinese noodles.

title: cheddar cheese roll
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese into softened cream cheese. Add pecans, red pepper, and garlic powder; mix well. Shape cheese mixture into two long rolls. Place chili powder on foil; roll the cheese rolls in chili powder until they are completely covered. Wrap each roll in foil and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Combine cream cheese and peanut butter in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Gradually add whipped topping and powdered sugar and continue beating until smooth.
Spoon filling into prepared crusts.
Freeze at least 8 hours or overnight.
Garnish with chocolate shavings, if desired.

title: italian beef supper
directions: *Or use
can (8 ounces) tomatoes and reduce water to 3/4 cup.

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring the sugar, syrup and water to a boil.
Add food coloring and peanuts.
Cook until hard boil stage.
Take off heat.
Add butter; beat until thick and loses gloss.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: granola bars
directions: In large bowl combine cereal, oats and raisins; set aside. In small saucepan combine brown sugar, corn syrup and honey. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla, blending until smooth.
Pour over cereal mixture; mix well.
If using chocolate chips, wait a few minutes before adding (otherwise they'll melt!).
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: mock beef stroganoff
directions: Cook
and drain macaroni (other pasta is just as good). Crumble
and
brown
ground beef in medium skillet.
Add onion and seasonings
and cook for 10 minutes; drain off any excess grease. Add
soups
and let come to a boil.
Add macaroni and let heat through.
Serves 6.
Note:	You can use other choices in soups - Cheddar cheese, cream of mushroom, cream of chicken or any of the soups for sauce.

title: tim's thunder cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients into creamy mixture.
Bake in 2 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with chocolate butter frosting.
Top with strawberries.

title: pot-roasted chicken
directions: Using kitchen string or heavy white thread, tie legs to tail of prepared chicken.
Hook wing tips under back.
Heat oil, butter and garlic in a large Dutch oven.
Brown the chicken; remove from pot. Add onions, potatoes and carrots to pan drippings and saute. Remove vegetables and reserve.
Stir broth, water, rosemary and pepper into pan drippings.
Return the chicken to the pan. Surround with vegetables.
Baste with the liquid; sprinkle vegetables with salt and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting twice with sauce or until chicken is fork-tender.
Serve chicken and vegetables with sauce.
(You may want to thicken sauce with a little cornstarch.)
Serves 4.

title: pink party punch
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
To serve, stir well.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale or carbonated drink. Yield: 1 gallon.

title: orange-jello salad
directions: Drain
pineapple.
Pour
cottage cheese in bowl and add dry Jell-O.
Add
pineapple.
Let
set while you chop oranges and pecans,
then add all of the other ingredients.
Mix well. Refrigerate preferably overnight.
This keeps well and is easy to carry.

title: dressing for tomatoes
directions: Mix together; pour over tomato slices and refrigerate at least 1 hour or more before serving.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Place sandwiches in large Pyrex dish.
Pour Kahlua over sandwiches.
Sprinkle on chopped nuts.
Top with Cool Whip. Place in freezer.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: italian zucchini crescent
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.

title: classic cheese tray
directions: Arrange ingredients on serving tray.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Top with extra grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low fat english trifle
directions: In glass bowl layer 1/2 of cake, pudding, and berries. Repeat layers and end with Cool Whip. Chill at least 2 hours. Serves 10.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil quickly and then reduce heat to medium and boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in oats, vanilla, nuts and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and let cool. Refrigerate.

title: quiche italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake pie crust for 6 to 8 minutes until set; allow to cool.
Layer pie crust with 3/4 cups of cheese, then spaghetti sauce, pepperoni, onion and remaining 3/4 cup cheese.
In a medium-sized bowl, combine eggs, cream, salt and pepper; mix thoroughly and pour over filling.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until top is golden and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 15 minutes; cut into wedges.
Yields 6 servings.
Preparation time:
1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Cook all but last 2 ingredients until thick.
Fill baked crust and use the egg whites beaten stiffly with 8 tablespoons sugar for meringue.

title: salad dressing for various salads
directions: Stir
together well. Note:
Will keep in the refrigerator for weeks;
better after setting awhile.
This dressing is delicious for cabbage slaw, carrot salad and apple salad.

title: hamburger pie
directions: In a skillet, melt Crisco.
Add meat and onion.
Cook just until meat is brown.
Stir in green beans, soup and seasonings. Pour this into pie shell and place other shell over filling.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press firmly into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan to make crust.
Add remaining ingredients as given and layer everything.
Add milk on top.
No mixing.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese potatoes
directions: Heat cream cheese, soup and milk over medium flame until cream cheese starts to melt.
Put hash browns in large 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour heated mixture over hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: seven day sweet pickles
directions: First Day:
Wash cucumbers and cover with boiling water.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Chop head of lettuce.
Then add rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice and pour over Jell-O.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts and heat, but do not boil.
Pour into a mold or other container and refrigerate until set.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple.
Add Cool Whip.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Brown meat in skillet, then put in casserole.
Add all other ingredients.
Amounts of pepper, celery and onion may be varied but total should equal 2 cups.
Garnish with round green pepper slices.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Cook macaroni. Add seasoning, tomatoes and cooked macaroni. Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over all and top with corn chips.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chile
directions: Dice bacon and fry until crisp; remove and set aside.
Cook onions and garlic until soft.
Add hamburg in chunks and cook until brown.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 45 minutes, uncovered.
Add bacon last.

title: swiss cheese bread
directions: Trim top and side crusts from bread, leaving bottom crusts intact.
Make 1-inch diagonal cuts through the bread, but do not cut through bottom crust.
Combine all ingredients and spread half of mixture between slices.
Use remaining half to frost top and sides.

title: orange-raisin-pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients in order listed. Mix just until blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until top is browned and pick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Wrap in plastic wrap or foil.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: gnocches(italian potato pasta)
directions: Growing up as a child, I always looked forward to the weekend trip to Grandma's house.
It was like mini vacations for the whole family.
Grandma is from the "old country," Italy.
Coming over at age 16, she also brought with her all the treasured recipes from there, from homemade ravioli to lasagna to homemade cookies.
One thing Grandma never does is use store bought sauce in her spaghetti, and on some special occasions, she hand makes her noodles.
Following is one of Grandma Vulpitta's many homemade recipes which I have come to know as the "World's Best" spaghetti and meatball sauce.

title: instant potato soup mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Store in an airtight container.
To serve:
Place 3 or 4 heaping tablespoons of mix in a bowl or mug.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Stir and let set for 2 minutes to thicken.
This is a good food item to carry to shut-ins and older people.
It is easy and economical, kinda like magic too.
I use whatever spices I have.

title: easy tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well and roll out.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees.

title: minute fudge frosting
directions: Place chocolate in saucepan along with sugar, milk, shortening and salt.
Bring slowly to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 1 minute.
Add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread.
Nutmeats can be added before pouring on cake.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Cube cheese and melt slowly over low heat in milk, stirring constantly.
When mixture is completely melted, mix water and cornstarch.
Pour into cheese mixture.
Continue stirring until thickened.
If needed, use more cornstarch with cold water to make thicker or milk to thin.

title: country ribs and homemade barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over ribs.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hawaiian cheese cake
directions: Bake the cake mix as directed.
Layer the pudding and pineapple.
Mix together the cream cheese and Cool Whip.
This is your third layer.
Sprinkle top with nuts.

title: cranberry salad(good)
directions: Cover fresh cranberries with water.
Cook until they stop popping.
Run through sieve or in blender, if you wish.
Add Jell-O.
Add sugar while hot.
Stir well.
Let cool and add crushed pineapple.
Add grapes and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: seasoned rice
directions: Saut onion, garlic and parsley in butter. Add rice, stirring well. Season to taste. Garnish with parsley after it is done. This rice can be served with a meat dish.

title: milky way cake
directions: Directions:
MELT TOGETHER 1 stick of butter, 8 Milky Way Bars (cut up).
CREAM TOGETHER 1 stick of butter, 1 Cup of sugar, 1 tsp. vanilla, 4 eggs.
DRY INGREDIENTS:
2 cups flour, WET INGREDIENTS: 1 and 1/4 cups buttermilk, 1 tsp. baking soda (stir in buttermilk). Alternately add dry and wet ingredients to cream ingredients.
Stir will after each addition.
ADD 1 cup chopped walnuts---stir.
ADD melted chocolate--stir.
POUR into a tube pan.
BAKE 325 until done.
Times vary.
At least an hour.
Then check every ten minutes.
Straw or wooden pick should come out clean.
Dark Chocolate Milky Way Bars work as well as regular Milky Way Bars in this recipe.

title: tamale pie
directions: Use large black skillet or a baking dish (if using baking dish, oil first).
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion to hamburger; let simmer.
Add corn, olives, tomato sauce, corn meal, water, milk and seasonings.
Stir well.
Spread cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bean and beef casserole
directions: Crumble corn beef into casserole dish.
Mix in undrained beans.
Stir in catsup to make a tomato sauce.
Add additional catsup, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat in microwave until hot. Serve with corn muffins and rice.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken and 1/2 teaspoon salt in Dutch oven.
Add water to cover.
Bring to boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes or until tender.
Bone chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Combine chicken with next 4 ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise and next 3 ingredients; add to chicken.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Garnish with fresh pineapple and strawberries.

title: easy pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add garlic and oregano.
Place biscuits on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten to 4-inch circles, leaving a rim.
Fill with tomato paste and then sausage.
Sprinkle with sharp cheese and then with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Makes 10.

title: coconut chess pie(2 pies)
directions: Chop coconut to very fine pieces. Mix as listed.
Stick bottom of pie shells with fork in several places.
Place pie shells in oven to dry out, 10 minutes in 325° oven.
Remove pie shells from oven and fill with mixture.
Bake in 325° oven for 35 minutes. Pies are done when tops are brown.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. If mixture is too stiff, add about 1/3 to 1/2 cup of milk. Pour mixture into a bread loaf baking pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.

title: oven-fried mushrooms
directions: Combine flour and paprika in plastic bag.
In another bag, mix bread crumbs, cheese and basil.
In a small bowl, beat eggs and milk lightly.
Wash and dry mushrooms.
Remove stems, if desired. Shake mushrooms in flour; dip in eggs.
Shake in crumbs.
Place bottom side down in lightly greased cookie sheet.
Drizzle melted butter or margarine over mushrooms.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with dipping sauce.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan. Simmer until flavors are blended. Pour into a unbaked pie crust. Roll a crust over the top; pierce with a fork and bake at 325 degree for 40 minutes. Put pie on a baking sheet in oven to prevent a mess.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Mix melted butter and garlic powder together; brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.
Great with seafood!!!

title: abby's cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Mix rest of the ingredients, except fruit, and pour over the margarine.
Spoon the fruit on top.

title: norwegian coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage and toss with salt; cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Heat sugar, vinegar and seeds.
Cook until sugar dissolves, about 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Add to cabbage.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Put in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: "souped up" pork chops
directions: Rub mustard on both sides of chops.
Roll in flour and brown on both sides.
Drain off fat.
Add chicken gumbo soup and cream of chicken soup.
Cover and cook on low heat until tender or bake in oven about 35 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes or steamed rice.

title: company potatoes
directions: In
a large bowl, mix potatoes and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Place in 3-quart casserole, greased, and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: mama's date loaf
directions: Note:
For best results, use heavy saucepan.
Mix sugar, margarine and milk together.
Place over medium heat until dissolved, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil; add chopped dates. Continue to cook until soft ball is formed when small amount is dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and beat until it begins to pile.
Add salt, vanilla and pecans.
Shape by hand into a roll 2 1/2 to 3-inches in diameter.
Wrap in wet towel which has been wrung out well.
Allow to stand until cool.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Do not refrigerate.
Cut as needed.
Wrap to store. Yields about 3 dozen.

title: bill's lasagne
directions: Chop onion and cook in pan on low heat.
Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Sprinkle Italian seasoning and garlic to taste. Add tomato sauce and tomato paste to meat and heat until hot.
In a large bowl add sauce to cottage cheese and Ricotta cheese and shredded Mozzarella.
Boil lasagna as directed until done.
Drain in a colander and rinse in cold water.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish, layer lasagne in bottom of dish.
Cover completely.
Add sauce, then sliced Mozzarella again, covering completely.
Repeat until you reach the top of dish.
Layer top with lasagne.

title: creole meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the chili sauce which you spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix well all these things and press in cake mold.
Line the pan with wax paper.
Place in and refrigerate overnight.
Turn out on a piece of foil.
Wrap up.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter-oatmeal bars
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cut in peanut butter and shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Mix egg, milk and vanilla; add to flour mixture with oats.
Mix well.
Spread in lightly greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Frost.

title: cheesy chicken with broccoli
directions: Spray a large skillet with nonstick spray.
Add the chicken and cook over medium heat until lightly browned.
Stir in the chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Stir in the macaroni and reduce heat to a medium boil.
Cover with a lid and let simmer 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Add the broccoli and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix in other ingredients; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with corn chips or nacho chips.
Pour beef mixture over chips; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Just before done, put Cheddar cheese on top and leave until melted.

title: easy sweet dill pickles
directions: Save the brine on the pickles and cut pickles into chunks. Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Add mixture to brine and stir until dissolved.
Put pickles back in jar.
Pour brine over pickles and shake; cover.
Let stand in refrigerator 3 days.
Great.

title: flower food
directions: Stir dry ingredients into warm water.
If you cannot find salt peter (potassium nitrate) at your pharmacy, check with a garden supply store.

title: pineapple-cherry-nut cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in pineapple, cherries and nuts.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes on a slightly greased pan.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Layer chicken on bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Combine cream of celery soup and cream of chicken soup; spread over chicken.
Combine the stuffing, egg, chicken broth, onion, margarine, salt and pepper; spread over the top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan baisers
directions: Beat egg white until soft peak forms.
Beat in brown sugar and vanilla gradually.
Fold in pecan halves & place on a greased cookie sheet in single layers.
Bake in 250 degree oven for 30 minutes.
Turn off heat and allow to cool in oven for 30 minutes. Break pecans apart and store in air tight container.

title: crispy onion rings
directions: Sift flour, meal and baking powder. Add oil, eggs and milk. Mix thoroughly. Dip onion rings into batter. Fry in vegetable oil for 2 to 3 minutes each side, until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: wilted salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces in a bowl.
Add thinly sliced red onion.
Fry bacon until entirely crisp; drain, saving grease.
Crumble bacon into salad.
Dissolve brown sugar in vinegar.
Pour this mixture alternately with hot grease over salad and toss.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions and rinse with cool water.
Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator.

title: berry punch
directions: Stir ingredients until well blended.
Serve very cold.

title: out of this world rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 c. warm water, let stand 10 minutes. Beat eggs and add dissolved yeast, 1 c. warm water, shortening, sugar and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Scrape down sides with wooden spoon.
Beat in 1/2 of flour to make soft dough.
Add rest of flour.
Cover and let double in volume (1 hour).
Punch down, cover, refrigerate overnight.
About 1 1/2 hours before baking, roll out dough to 1/2 inch thick.
Cover with soft butter.
Roll. Slice 1 inch thick.
Place cut side down.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese until softened.
Stir in other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: brian's broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and margarine in large skillet until tender.
Add soup, evaporated milk and cheese; mix well.
Bring to a boil. Stir in broccoli and rice.
Spoon into deep round baking dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter. In a large bowl, combine powdered sugar and cereal. Mix peanut butter mixture and cereal mixture. Blend together with hands. Form the mixture into 1/2-inch balls. Chill until they are firm. Melt chocolate according to instructions on the bag. Dip balls in melted chocolate. Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: kinnikinnick berry jelly
directions: Wash berries and cover with water.
Boil about 20 minutes. Strain.
Measure sugar into a dry dish.
Measure 4 cups juice and vinegar into a large kettle.
Add pectin.
Stir well and bring to a boil.
Add measured sugar and mix well.
Continue stirring and bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil jelly exactly 2 minutes. Remove from heat and pour into prepared jars.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.
Can add raisins, nuts, M&M's, or any thing you would like.

title: lentil-tomato soup
directions: Put all ingredients (except the tomatoes) into a large pot and simmer 3 hours.
Add more water if needed.
Stir in the tomatoes at the end.
Serves 11 cups.

title: marble squares
directions: Cream the butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Add walnuts.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chips over top. Bake at 350° for 2 minutes and then remove from the oven.
Run a knife through dough to marbleize.
Return to the oven and bake an additional 12 to 14 minutes or until sides begin to loosen from the pan.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well. Add soda to buttermilk and add baking powder and salt to flour. Add buttermilk and flour mixture about half at a time and beat well until mixed.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Can make into muffins.
Will keep well in icebox for several days.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese, then add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, then blend in flour and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crab ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and crab meat.
Form into large ball.
Coat with cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: german beer coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, cinnamon, allspice and cloves. Set aside. In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add flour mixture, alternating with beer, blending well after each addition.
Stir in dates and nuts. Pour into well-greased 12-cup fluted tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Turn out on a rack to cool. Wrap in foil for 24 hours before serving. May sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Serve with Rum Butter Spread.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet, drain.
Mix together with noodles and tomato soup.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake 10 minutes in 350° oven until cheese begins to melt.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: zucchini squash glaze
directions: Simmer together all ingredients, except cornstarch for 5 minutes.
Add and thicken with cornstarch. Cook 1 minute or until clear.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line two 9 x 6-inch pans with aluminum foil and spray with Pam.
Cream the confectioners sugar, salt and butter.
Add 2 cups of flour; shape into 2 balls and spread on aluminum foil.

title: apple cake
directions: In large bowl, mix well the oil, eggs and sugar.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Mix well (use a spoon, this will be thick).
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°
for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Let set a day for added flavor.

title: party mix
directions: Mix Crispix, Oh's, pretzels and pecans.
Spoon over butter, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Mix together and sprinkle on top the salt, garlic and onion; stir.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours, tossing every 30 minutes.
This will make a large turkey roaster pan full.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften
overnight.
Cream butter and sugar; add cheese. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour slowly, then vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fondue
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Heat and serve with French bread cubes.

title: chickpeas with pasta
directions: Pour all contents from chickpeas, including liquid, into 6 or 8-cup saucepan.
Add 3 cups water, garlic, salt, pepper, oil, sauce and oregano.
Simmer until chickpeas are tender, about 30 minutes.
Cook pasta separately and drain well.
Add to main ingredients when done.
Let simmer another 5 minutes so the pasta will absorb the flavor.

title: full o' boloney
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except cheese in
1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake, covered, 1 hour and 15 minutes. Remove cover; top with cheese.
Broil until bubbly and browned. Yield:
4 servings.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until stems are almost tender, 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.
Place broccoli in ungreased 1 1/2-quart round casserole dish.
Heat oven to 400°. Beat milk and soup until smooth.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix baking mix and margarine until crumbly; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until crumbs are light brown, about 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Spread rhubarb in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and gelatin. Sprinkle with dry cake mix. Pour water and melted butter over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Put together as listed and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Let stand 15 minutes.
Put in round cake pan or quiche pan or 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven. Serves 6.

title: sausage cheese casserole
directions: Slice bread in quarters.
Butter and place buttered side down in 8 x 12 x 2 casserole.
Brown sausage; crumble and drain. Scatter over bread.
Mix milk, eggs, paprika, nutmeg, salt, and worcestershire sauce.
Add cheese and mushrooms and pour over bread.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Remove one hour before baking.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Add packaged jello, water, lemon juice and juice from oranges; stir.
Let stand in refrigerator until thick and syrupy.
Add oranges; stir.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in another bowl.
Let stand in refrigerator until firm.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together ingredients several times.
Dissolve one cake or package of yeast into 1/2 cup of lukewarm water.
Cut into dry ingredients the vegetable shortening.
Add buttermilk, water and yeast mixture. Work together until all flour is moistened.
Cover and refrigerate.
Use as needed.
Will keep for one week or longer.
To use, roll out on floured board 1/2-inch thick.
Cut for biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until brown.

title: baked apple pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine melted butter and dry cake mix.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of this for top crust.
Pat the rest into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with combined peanut butter and marshmallow cream and spread evenly.
Crumble remaining mixture over that.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: islandic pancakes with whipped cream
directions: Beat together all ingredients and mix in the stiffly beaten egg whites last.
Bake paper thin on a hot cast-iron griddle. Spread with preserves, jam or jelly, and one tablespoon whipped cream.
Fold into triangles.
Serve with afternoon coffee or as a dessert.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; put into a baking dish.

title: ham rollups
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing mix. If needed, add 1 or 2 tbsp milk to thin. Spread mixture on ham slices. Roll up starting from short side. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. Slice into thin rolls. Arrange on a platter to serve.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Add cornstarch and sugar together.
Dissolve in water.
Boil mixture until thick.
Take off heat when thick.
Add 3 tablespoons jello.
Cool.
Add strawberries to mixture and pour into baked pie shell.
Add topping before serving.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Cook all ingredients until bubbly, stirring constantly. Reduce heat; cook for 5 minutes and serve.

title: tasty apples
directions: Peel apples and quarter.
Add water, sugar and vinegar. Cook until partially done.
Sprinkle in Jell-O and cook until done.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine all and refrigerate overnight.
Drain to serve, if desired.

title: snow pea salad(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Blanch snow peas 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain.
Rinse with cold running water to stop cooking.
Let cool.
In a large glass bowl, combine snow peas, pepper rings and mushrooms.
In a small container, combine oil, vinegar, sugar and lemon juice.
Just before serving, toss vegetable mixture with oil mixture.
Sprinkle sesame seed on top.

title: veal piccata
directions: Pound veal lightly.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and dredge in flour.
Melt butter in skillet and brown veal quickly, turning once.
Don't try to cook all the veal at once; it probably won't fit.
Remove veal.
Place on warm platter and pour off excess fat. Add 3 tablespoons of water and scrape up brown residue.
Add lemon juice.
Pour sauce over meat and sprinkle with parsley. Garnish with lemon slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: black walnut jello cake
directions: Mix ingredients well for 5 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in tube pan.

title: no-weep meringue
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Cook until clear.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks.
Add cooked mixture and continue beating. Add sugar gradually and beat until stiff peaks.
Cover pie; seal edges and bake at 325° until brown.
I find this makes enough for 6 egg whites.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Separate broccoli in bite-size pieces; add all ingredients. Better if it stands for a few hours.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes(crock-pot method)
directions: Put half of potatoes, onions and ham in crock-pot.
Repeat layering with remaining half of potatoes, onions and ham. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Spoon soup over all (undiluted).
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or high for 4 to 5 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: western barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shake well and use as a base for any kind of meat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix margarine, broth and soup together and pour over chicken.
Mix the flour and buttermilk together and drop on chicken.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: maryland style crabcakes
directions: Take bread crumbs after putting them through the food processor and toast in 200° oven until dried out.
Pick shells from crabmeat, then mix remaining ingredients together until smooth consistency.
Mix in crabmeat.
Add bread crumbs, starting with 3 cups and add more until a soft dough is formed.
Be careful not to break up crabmeat.
Cook under broiler on both sides until lightly browned.
Serve with tartar sauce or cocktail sauce.

title: no peek chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice, soup, water, parsley and curry in well buttered casserole.
Lay chicken on top.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Seal tightly with heavy-duty foil; bake at 350° for 2 1/4 hours.
Don't peek.
Slivered, toasted almonds may be sprinkled over the top just before serving.
This is a never fail casserole when you have guests and want to take the work out of cooking.
Serve with a green vegetable, tossed salad and dessert.

title: dump cake
directions: Lightly grease an oblong pan.
Place ingredients in pan, one ingredient at a time, in the order listed.
Slice butter and layer on top.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown.

title: spicy eggnog
directions: Combine sugar, allspice, cinnamon and 1/8 teaspoon nutmeg.
In large bowl of electric mixer, at high speed, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in half of sugar mixture until stiff peaks form.
In small bowl, beat egg yolks until lemon color. Gradually beat in remaining sugar mixture until thick and smooth. Thoroughly fold into whites.
Stir in milk and cream, mix well. Serve well chilled, each serving sprinkled with nutmeg.
Add spirits to your own preference.

title: mom's chili sauce
directions: Scald and peel tomatoes; let set in kettle until settled. Pour off excess water.
Add all other ingredients.
Boil until thick and bottle.
Optional:
1 or 2 sweet red peppers, chopped.

title: peanut butter-potato candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Roll out flat and spread with a thin layer of peanut butter.
Roll up and chill until firm.
Slice into 1/4 or 1/2-inch pieces.

title: blender quiche
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Pour into a greased pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Knife test. Let stand 5 minutes before eating.
Can add sausage that has been browned and drained before adding to mixture.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix together in pan and cook for 1 hour.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and let cool.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Fold in whipping cream.
Put into mold and refrigerate.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Combine next 9 ingredients, and add to meat.
Simmer until onions and peppers soften.
Combine the cold water and cornstarch to make a paste; stir into mixture, and cook until thickened.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: no milk potato-broccoli soup
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients in a pan with water to cover. Cook until potatoes are done.
In a blender, mix the cashews, water and flour until smooth and creamy.
Add to potatoes.
Can add more mixture if you want soup thicker.

title: freezer ready coleslaw
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, water and celery seed to a boil then cool.
Add remaining ingredients to cabbage.
Pour on dressing. This is ready to serve or freeze.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add extract, 7-Up and flour alternately.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: Melt margarine and cook onion and mushrooms until tender.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Add rice; cover and cook 25 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: chocolate peanutty pie
directions: Gradually blend milk into peanut butter in small bowl, beating until smooth.
Blend in pie filling mix and beat until blended and smooth (1 to 2 minutes).
Fold in whipped topping and nuts.
Spoon into pie shell.
Freeze 1 hour or chill 3 hours before serving. Garnish with additional whipped topping and peanut halves, if desired.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Stir and bake 10 more minutes.
Easy to microwave, cook 5 minutes, then stir and cook 5 more minutes.
Serve with dip size taco chips.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix thoroughly corn and onion.
Stir in slowly until consistency of cake batter 1/2 to 1 cup milk.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole.
Top with reserved cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.
Can be increased to serve any number.

title: ham-potato scallop
directions: Cook onion in oleo until soft; add soup, milk and parsley. Mix well.
Add potatoes.
Place 1/3 of mixture in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; add 1 cup of ham in a layer.
Repeat layers; end with potato mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: brer rabbit molasses muffins
directions: Combine bran, milk, and molasses.
Let stand until most of moisture is absorbed.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat well.
Add raisins.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to softened mixture.
Put into greased muffin pans, 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes until lightly brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: i cannot tell a lie pie
directions: Grease casserole dish and pour in pie filling.
Mix cake mix with oatmeal.
Pour dry ingredients over the cherry pie mixture. Drizzle melted butter or margarine over all and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: authentic tacos
directions: Roll meat in flour and place in stock pot filled with 1/4-inch water.
Brown meat and cook on low heat for about 30 minutes.
Then roll up and heat to high and add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 hour longer until meat is shredding.
Serve in flour tortillas and garnish with lettuce and picante sauce.

title: cheese pie (eggs) for hannah
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish. Beat milk and flour together.
Then add eggs and seasonings and beat.
Stir in 1/2 of the cheese and vegetables or meat.
Pour in pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and puffy, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and return to oven for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: zesty mexican soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients except cilantro; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Stir in cilantro.
Serves 6.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients and press into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan

title: icebox rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir until salt and everything is dissolved.
Cool to warm.
Add yeast, which has been dissolved in warm water, and beaten egg.
Mix well. Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Rub surface with oil or shortening and store in the refrigerator.
Take out the amount needed, knead well, roll, cut, butter, put on pan, cover and let rise 1 hour, until doubled.
Bake.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: Rinse cooked pasta in cold water. Transfer to large bowl.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Keep this on low
burner
on
the stove or over a flame warmer.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook and whip potatoes and butter.
