Add remaining ingredients and whip thoroughly, until light and fluffy.
Place in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with green onion flakes and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Can be refrigerated and baked later.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Reserve 1/3 cup of the crumbs.
Press mixture into bottom of square pan or baking dish.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Use any good cake recipe
to make 4 layers.
Bake 2 plain, then add raisins, nut meats, cinnamon and cloves.
When cool stick with filling.

title: mixed supper
directions: Saute onion and green pepper until soft; set aside.
Cook kielbasa for 20 to 25 minutes, then cut in small pieces.
Mix with onion and pepper and fry for 10 minutes.
Add pork and beans.
Mix well.
Heat until hot.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix until well blended. Pour batter into greased 10-inch Bundt pan (microwave-proof). Microwave on 100% power 11 to 14 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Spray 9x13 pan. Mix rhubarb and sugar together and put in bottom of pan. Over the top of this sprinkle jello. Then sprinkle the dry cake mix over this. Take melted butter and pour over the top along with 1/2 c. water. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: nacho dip
directions: Use quiche dish and spread ingredients in thin layers starting with the cream cheese and ending with Jack cheese.
Serve with nacho flavor tortilla chips.

title: frosty fruit smoothie
directions: In blender, combine yogurt, peaches, banana, wheat germ, orange juice, ice cubes and sugar (sweetener) and blend one minute or until smooth.
Serve immediately, poured into tall glasses and topped with peach and banana slices and sprinkled with wheat germ. A cool and guilt-free treat anytime!

title: hot dish(serves 90- 1 nesco full)
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Cook spaghetti and combine all ingredients together.
Put butter on top and bake about 2 hours at 350°.

title: scalloped corn and oysters
directions: If you want more oysters, add a can, drained.

title: johnny cake
directions: Beat egg slightly and add the sugar and salt.
Stir the soda into the sour milk and add the sugar and egg mixture.
Add the flour and corn meal and stir until blended.
Bake in a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan or buttered individual pans at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: welsh pumpkin bread
directions: In a large bowl, cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin. Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine dry mixture and pumpkin mixture, blending well.
Pour into two greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool at least 10 minutes before cutting.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Cover chicken breast with saran wrap and beat until flat. Lay slice of ham on each piece.
Cream together cream cheese and herbs.
Funnel cream mixture on top of ham.
Place slice of bell pepper on top.
Using a small piece of saran wrap, roll breast slices into tube shapes.
Heat oil in pan.
Brown breasts 5 to 8 minutes on each side, or until done.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Blend almond meal, water, salt and vanilla ingredients, then chill.
When chilled, then blend ripe bananas and honey into it until creamy and smooth.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Melt butter; add onions and saute.
Add chicken and cook both sides until white on both sides (about 10 minutes on both sides). Add whipping cream, olives (drained) and wine.
Stir, cover and cook on low for about one hour or longer.
The more it simmers, the better it is!
Serve over rice.

title: chicken crescent squares
directions: Heat oven according to crescent roll package.
Mix cream cheese, 1 1/2 tablespoons butter and milk.
Add drained chicken and mix (salt and pepper to taste).
Unroll crescent rolls and break at perforations to form 4 squares (2 diamonds per square). Pinch perforations together.
Place chicken mixture on flattened roll.
Bring corners of rolls together; pinch to seal.
Melt remaining butter and drizzle over squares.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake as directed on crescent roll package (approximately 17 minutes).

title: velveeta vegetable bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook broccoli until just heated through. Mix broccoli and cheese. Spoon into greased baking dish. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 3-quart casserole.
In 3-quart saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Add zucchini, carrots, celery and onion.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 5 minutes or until celery is crisp-tender.
Drain.
In small bowl, combine sour cream, dill weed and soup.
Add to cooked vegetables; mix.
In large bowl combine stuffing mix and margarine.
Spoon half of stuffing in bottom of prepared casserole.
Spoon vegetable mixture over stuffing mixture; sprinkle with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and thoroughly heated.

title: peas and macaroni shells
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil and margarine.
Add shells, peas, parsley, salt and pepper and mix well.
Put in casserole. Cover and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fruit trifle
directions: Slice strawberries and mix with sugar; set aside.
Combine milk, sour cream and pudding mix.
Beat, scraping down sides of bowl.
Do not overbeat.
Mixture will thicken in about one minute. Position half the slices into the bottom and partially up sides of 3-quart serving dish.
Drizzle orange juice.
Cover with half of pudding and then half of strawberries.
Repeat layers. Decorate surface with whip cream.
Refrigerate.

title: raisin bread(bread machine)
directions: Put all the ingredients except half of the raisins in the inner pan in order for your machine.
Select bread setting.
Add the remaining raisins when the machine beeps.

title: cajun baked beans
directions: Brown in skillet ground beef, onion and bell pepper and add to taste:
salt, pepper, cayenne pepper and garlic powder.
Mix ground beef mixture with beans and add to taste:
brown sugar, mustard and ketchup.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or in microwave on High for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon roasted nuts
directions: Melt butter and add pecans to it. Set aside. Mix egg whites, sugar and salt. Pour pecan mixture onto cookie sheet, then pour sugar mixture over it. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes. Stir every 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: snoopy's hot dogs
directions: Open crescent rolls; set aside.
Open hot dogs; set aside. Open American cheese slices; set aside.
Center cheese in middle of one crescent roll, then place hot dog on edge of cheese roll.
Do this with all remaining rolls, hot dogs and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until rolls are golden brown.
Serve immediately with mustard and catsup.
Makes 8 to 12.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Form 2 rolls.
Use foil (shiny side to meat) to wrap meat.
Let set 24 hours in refrigerator.
Bake on broiling rack for 2 hours at 325°.
Cool.

title: molded cranberry ring
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar, set aside.
Dissolve Jello in hot water and add pineapple juice, chill until partially set.
Add cranberry mixture, pineapple, walnuts and celery.
Chill until completely set.
Unmold on crisp lettuce.

title: chicken yum-yum casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except potato chips.
Put in baking dish (greased).
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: artic freeze
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well, then fold in 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Pour into lightly greased container and freeze until ready to use.

title: mary schott's bean salad
directions: Put all ingredients into a large container, layering each ingredient and sprinkling with oil, vinegar and pepper.
Spread garlic carefully over each layer. When ingredients are used up, put a tablespoon of mayonnaise in several places on top of ingredients.
Mix gently and chill. Turn bowl upside down several times.
Marinate several hours or overnight.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla with mixer for 10 minutes. Spread on crust.
Slice 5 to 7 bananas on mixture.
Then spread 1 can crushed pineapple on top with one container of Cool Whip.
Add cherries and nuts to garnish.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Line tube pan with waxed paper.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While warm, poke holes in cake with a straw.
Combine coconut milk and Eagle Brand milk; pour over cake.
When cool, frost cake with Cool Whip and shredded coconut.

title: poulet francais
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all vegetables together and steam until tender.
Mix the chicken and the mushroom soup together in a large bowl.
Add the steamed vegetables to the chicken mixture. Add salt, pepper, garlic powder, onion powder and red wine to the mixture; mix well.

title: tony's tiger bites(microwave)
directions: In a 4-quart microwave-safe bowl, melt marshmallows and margarine on High 3 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking. Stir in peanut butter until mixture is smooth.
Add Kellogg's Frosted Flakes cereal, stirring until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into 1 1/2 x 2-inch bars. Yield:
About 32 bars.

title: green pea guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender or food processor until peas are pureed.
Blend in tomato and onion.
Spoon in container and garnish with cilantro or diced chiles.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, 1 cup milk and 1 cup sugar.
Do not use metal spoon!
Do not cover! Do not refrigerate!

title: coconut carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Add flour mixture; beat until smooth.
Add pineapple, carrots, coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: icebox cake
directions: In saucepan, melt over low heat marshmallows with milk.
Then add graham cracker crumbs.
Stir.
Add remaining ingredients and press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mixture will be sticky.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: honey apple torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine honey and lemon juice in a large nonstick skillet; bring to a simmer over medium heat. Add apples and cook for 14 minutes or until almost tender, stirring frequently. Beat 3/4 cup granulated sugar, butter, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in lemon rind. Lightly spoon flour into a dry measuring cup. Combine the flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually add flour mixture to sugar mixture. Pour batter into a 9-inch spring-form pan coated with cooking spray. Remove apples from skillet with a slotted spoon. Discard remaining liquid. Arrange apple slices spoke like on top of batter, pressing slices gently into the batter. Combine 1 tablespoon granulated sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan on wire rack. Cut into wedges, using a serrated knife. Yields 10 servings.

title: coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9-inch tube pan.
In small bowl, mix walnuts, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Set aside.

title: mark's spaghetti sauce
directions: In Dutch
oven,
brown
in olive oil ground beef, onion and garlic.
Add
sauce,
paste
and water and then add spices and cheese.
Cook
over
low for 2 hours or until cooked down. Add red wine and cook another hour.
Use for any pasta dish.

title: nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix first 4 ingredients.
Beat hard for 30 seconds.
Stir in nuts.
(Batter will be lumpy.) Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until toothpick stuck into center comes out clean.
Crack in top is typical.
Cool before slicing.
Cool on wire racks.

title: fruit punch
directions: Add ginger ale just before serving.
Make ice ring using some of the punch before adding ginger ale.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and let stand in refrigerator several hours. Good with all types of new vegetables for example squash, cucumbers, carrots, broccoli or cauliflower.

title: fresh pork sausage
directions: Garlic should be chopped very fine with a knife or pulverized in a blender.

title: party salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk in a large bowl and refrigerate one hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well and refrigerate overnight.

title: old-fashioned biscuit pudding
directions: Pour milk over biscuits and let stand until they get soft. Beat eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add to biscuits and milk. Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° until firm and brown on top.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown italian sausage in skillet with 1/2 c onion and 2 cloves minced garlic.
In large pot bring water, buillion cubes and crushed tomatoes to a slow boil.
Drain grease from sausage and add to pot.
Stir in carrots, zucchini, italian seasoning, and the remaining onions and minced garlic.
Cover and boil over medium high heat for 35-40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add garbanzo beans and pasta and continue to boil for 15 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa.
Slightly beat eggs; add to sugar and cocoa.
Add melted margarine and milk.
Stir until mixed well. Pour in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Top with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cube cheese.
Place in a 2-quart microwavable bowl.
Add can of tomatoes and chiles.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and cook 2 more minutes.
When cheese is melted, serve with chips.

title: two crust raisin pie
directions: Place raisins and water in a saucepan. Heat to boil.

Remove from fire; drain off liquid and add gradually to flour, cornstarch and sugar which has been mixed well. Add this paste to raisins and cook until thick. Roll out pie pastry and line 8-inch pie pan. Pour in raisins and dot with butter. Cover with upper crust. Brush with cream or milk. Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes, then at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fried cabbage
directions: In iron skillet add olive oil, cabbage, salt, pepper, sugar and water. Cover and let cook for 5 minutes. Add soda and cook 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove bones and skin. Boil broth and add vegetables and seasoning.
Add chicken and noodles. Simmer until most of the liquid is gone and noodles are tender.
Pour in casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hungarian pork paprika
directions: Combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Toss with meat.
In skillet, brown meat in hot oil.
Stir in tomatoes.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat 20 minutes or until meat is tender, stirring frequently.
Remove pan from heat.
Remove 1/2 cup of sauce mixture from skillet and blend with sour cream.
Return mixture to skillet; blend well.
DO NOT BOIL!
Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: grammie's biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together 4 times.
Mix in shortening, breaking it up with a fork.
Stir in milk to form a ball.
Roll out on floured board, not too thin, about 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick. Cut with a biscuit cutter and place biscuits, not touching each other, on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: halloween bars
directions: Melt butter.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer the rest of the ingredients in order given.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool on rack before cutting.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box, using 2 (9-inch) cake pans. Cool. Split layers with knife or dental floss. Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth. Spread 1/3 of mixture between each
layer as you stack them on plate. Put in the refrigerator until chilled. Frost with chocolate frosting. Chill until ready to serve.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
Form into a rectangular log.
Roll in chili powder.
Chill.
Good with Triscuits or Wheat Thins.

title: gone-all-day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water/wine and flour until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
When ready to serve, adjust seasoning.
Serve over noodles or rice or with crunchy French bread.
Serves 8.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Chill several hours to blend flavors.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: beef jerky
directions: Remove all fat from steak. Slice 1/8-inch thick. Combine marinating ingredients and marinate overnight in a shallow glass dish in the refrigerator. Turn the meat occasionally.

Drain meat well on paper towels. Lay strips in a single layer on oven rack. Place a cookie sheet or foil underneath to catch drippings. Roast at lowest possible temperature (120° to 140°) for 8 to 12 hours with oven door slightly ajar. Taste occasionally until jerky is as chewy as desired. Recipe makes 1/2 pound. Store in a plastic bag.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix mayonnaise and chili sauce.
Add eggs, olives and spices. Stir and serve over lettuce salad.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: spaghetti pizza style
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Toss with spaghetti.
Spread mixture in an 8 x 11-inch greased pan.
Pour sauce over.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: chips ahoy dessert
directions: Dip each Chips Ahoy cookie quickly into milk and layer in a 5 x 7-inch baking dish, alternating each layer with Cool Whip. Shave chocolate bars over top and refrigerate several hours.
Cut into squares.
Enjoy!

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine beef, rice, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of mixture in shallow baking pan (13 x 9 1/2-inch).
Combine soup and water.
Pour over meat.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken noodle bake
directions: In a saucepan cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in rest of ingredients except cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: lena's paprika chicken
directions: Wash the chicken well and drain.
Brown the onions lightly in the fat; add the paprika and the chicken.
Sprinkle with salt. Add tomatoes and green pepper.
Cover and cook slowly about 1 hour or until tender.
Pour sour cream over the chicken.
Do not let it boil.
Serve with freshly boiled soft noodles.
Hungarian recipe.

title: lime-strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix strawberry jello in 1 cup hot water. Add frozen strawberries.
Let set until congealed.
Spread sour cream on top of jello.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Line cupcake pans with 24 cupcake liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fill the liners 3/4 full with cheese mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Top each with spoonful of filling.
Chill.
Serves 24.

title: green rice
directions: Add oil to beaten eggs.
Add this and all other ingredients to rice.
Bake in two shallow greased baking dishes at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yield::
10 servings.

title: king tut's pudding
directions: Spread cookie crumbs in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan, combine dates, water and salt; bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Cool at room temperature. Stir in nuts.
Spread mixture over crumbs.
Combine vanilla and cream; whip stiff.
Spread over dates.
Chill overnight.
Cut in squares to serve.
(Very rich.)

title: white christmas fruit cake
directions: Beat butter, margarine, sugar, egg yolks and extracts well. Mix in 2 1/2 cups flour (dredge fruit and nuts with the other 1/2 cup).
Don't chop nuts or fruit.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter, then add the fruit and nuts to the batter and mix well.
In a tube pan, bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Increase heat to 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Leave in oven 7 minutes.
Remove and cool in pan.
When cool, wrap in foil and store airtight in cool place.
Bake at least 10 days before holidays.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, soup and 1 cup broth in 2-quart casserole.
Top with dressing mixed with beaten egg and 1 cup broth.
Bake covered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peach delight
directions: Break cake in bite-size pieces.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread 1/4 over cake pieces.
Mix 2 cups peaches (fresh or canned) with glaze.
Spread over cake.
Top with rest of Cool Whip and cream cheese.
(Strawberries and strawberry glaze may be used in place of peaches.)

title: pasta fruit salad
directions: Cook, drain and rinse pasta following package directions. Drain fruit juices into a glass bowl.
Beat in eggs, sugar and flour.
Cook in microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes, until mixture boils and thickens, stirring several times.
Cool 10 minutes.
Mix everything but Cool Whip and fresh fruit. Refrigerate overnight.
Add Cool Whip and fresh fruit just before serving.

title: berry burst
directions: Combine and blend in processor or blender.
Omit honey if using sweetened flavored yogurt.
This is a nutritious, low calorie snack drink.

title: cauliflower scramble(czechoslovakia)
directions: In a large skillet melt butter; saute onion until tender.
Add cauliflower, stirring occasionally until heated through.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper; pour over cauliflower mixture.
Cook until set.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Add melted butter, rind, juice and beaten egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Heat over medium heat until thick.
Let cool; fold in sour cream.
Pour into pie shell. Chill at least 3 hours before serving.
Top with whipped cream.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat together peaches, 1 cup sugar and margarine until hot and margarine is melted.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together flour, 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder and milk.
This makes a thin batter.
Pour over hot fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, spinach, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Put in greased flat-type casserole.
Place cut tomatoes on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 450° oven.
Makes 6 layers.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, pepper and mushrooms.
Add soup, undiluted.
Place in casserole; top with potatoes and cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ragu gazpacho
directions: Mix Ragu and water in bowl.
Stir in onions, peppers and cucumbers.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
When ready to serve, cut bread into cubes and toast until light brown.
Serve in bowls and sprinkle toasted bread cubes on top.

title: greek honey puffs
directions: Dissolve yeast in tepid water.
Combine the rest of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Add the yeast mixture to ingredients and beat at high speed until a smooth dough is formed.
Cover and place in warm place until batter rises 2 to 3 times original amount.
When dough has risen, moisten 1 hand with water and take a handful of dough.
Squeeze your fist until a small ball is formed and with a spoon, ease it into the hot oil.
Fry a few at a time.
Remove when brown with slotted spoon; drain on paper towel. Transfer to serving dish and pour hot honey over balls.
Can sprinkle with cinnamon and nuts.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease rectangular pan, 13 X 9 X 2. Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms, beat 20 strokes.
Pat in pan with floured hands, pressing 1/2 inch up sides.
Layer well-drained ground beef, tomatoes, and green peppers on dough. Mix remaining ingredients and spoon over top.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake until brown.
Cooking Time:
25 - 30 minutes.

title: spatzles(only if having gravy with your meal.)
directions: Bring a pot of water to a boil.
Add salt to water only.
Make sure the flour and eggs are mixed together; add a little water if needed.
Batter should be thick.
Put batter on cutting board. With an egg turner slice thin, long chunks into boiling water. When they swell and float to top, wait 5 minutes.
Take them out; put in bowl (glass).
Add butter and crumbs.
Repeat until batter is all used.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a very large bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing after each addition, until well blended.
Drop by rounded tablespoon on cookie sheet. Only 6 cookies per sheet. Bake for 12 minutes.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Mix with hands until bowl is clean.
Pinch portions the size of nickels and roll in sesame seed.
Make dent with finger.
Fill with jam or preserves (something tart, example plum).
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until golden but not brown.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large skillet; cook over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender. Add salt, pepper and sugar to cabbage. Stir gently.

title: marinated pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Wash and cook cauliflower in boiling water about 3 minutes with carrots.
In a bowl, mix pasta, cauliflower and carrots with chopped cucumber, bell pepper and celery.
Toss well with Italian dressing and chill overnight. Before serving, add cherry tomatoes and toss again.

title: no-bake cheesecake pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt chips over medium-low heat; stir until smooth.
Remove from the heat; stir in cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into the crust.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or until set.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix the yeast with the milk and sugar. Sift together the flour, soda, and salt. Cut in shortening. Mix in yeast mixture and stir until ingredients are moist. Knead four or five times, then roll about 1/2 inch thick and cut with

biscuit cutter. Dip in melted butter and placed on greased cookie sheet. Let rise, covered, about one hour. Bake in a preheated 350° oven about 12 minutes or until nicely browned. Makes about 3 dozen 1/2 inch biscuits.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Makes 36.

title: squash casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 14-inch baking dish with Pam.
Cook squash and onion until tender; drain well.
Mash with potato masher.
Add all other ingredients.
Sprinkle small amount of grated cheese over top.
Bake at 350° in oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mama's dressing
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Pour	the ingredients around the
baking
bird
the last few minutes it bakes.
Bake the dressing until done.
By trial and error you can learn how much (if
any)
of the meat drippings you wish to leave in the pan as you pour the dressing on top of it.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into 6 patties.
Fry in small amount of cooking oil until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: In baking dish, place in layers pork and beans, chili with beans and hot tamales.
Cut in half with meal side up.
Place in oven and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: mamie's tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add beaten egg, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix and add flour (may need more flour for a stiff enough dough to roll out).
Bake at 275° until edges are brown.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Gradually add vanilla, eggs and syrup. Sprinkle pecans in pie shell.
Pour filling over pecans.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes longer, or until pie is set.

title: scrambled egg bake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add parsley, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Scramble to moist stage.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan: scrambled eggs, sour cream, cooked meat, cheese, onions and mushrooms.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick borsch
directions: Place beets and half the beet liquid in blender.
Add remaining ingredients and blend until smooth.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Serve garnished with a dollop of sour cream and a pinch of chopped tarragon or parsley.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar, eggs, buttermilk and flavoring; beat well.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° until not shaky or as brown as desired.

title: mother goose popcorn
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients 4 minutes.
Set aside 1 or 2 minutes. Pour over popcorn.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften margarine and cheese.
Mix all ingredients except Rice Krispies.
Add Rice Krispies last.
Shape into balls slightly smaller than an English walnut.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes on an ungreased sheet.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clams.
Combine all ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Can be served chilled or warm.

title: mustard tomato pie(main course)
directions: Put pie crust in pie plate.
Spread mustard generously on crust.
Layer Swiss cheese, then sliced tomatoes; sprinkle olive oil and basil over all.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Fold the edge of crust over about 1 inch.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lemony steamed fish
directions: Center each fillet on 12-inch square foil.
Sprinkle with onion, parsley, dill weed, paprika, salt, pepper and lemon juice. Fold foil over each fillet to make pocket; pleat seams to securely enclose; place on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated moderate (375°) oven for 30 minutes.

title: potato surprise
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix all ingredients.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with 2 cups crushed Ritz crackers.
Drizzle 1 stick melted margarine over crackers.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: raspberry spinach salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and shake well before using.

title: bubble n' squeak
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, cabbage and chopped bacon.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in well-greased frying pan and fry.

title: baked pasta with 3 cheeses
directions: Cook pasta following package directions.
Drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onion.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Layer potatoes, onion and cheese.
Salt and pepper.
Layer until everything is used.
Pour milk over mixture.
Cover and bake at 400° for 2 hours.

title: cinnamon disc grandma willette
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mold into balls.
Roll in a mixture of chopped nuts and cinnamon.
Place on greased baking sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove right away from baking sheet.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix hot water mixture with flour and yeast.
Beat.
Then add 2 eggs. Then add 3 to 3 1/2 cups more flour.
Just enough so it will still be kind of sticky.
Put in refrigerator over night. This makes very good hot rolls and cinnamon rolls, caramel nut rolls & coffeecakes, etc.

title: big sky beef
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion; drain. Mix in the taco seasoning mix and water, bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Add tomato sauce and kidney beans; simmer for 10 minutes. Spread 1 cup of the corn chips in baking dish. Layer with half of the meat mixture. Next layer with half of the cheddar cheese. Spread second cup of corn chips and repeat layers. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: bake chicken supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut up fryer.
Place in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake chicken in oven for 45 minutes (turning once) until golden brown.
Combine other ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over baked chicken pieces.
Place aluminum foil over pan.
Return to oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pepper twists
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, pepper and salt.
Cut in margarine or butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in the center.
Add broth; stir just until dough clings together.

title: chicken divan
directions: In 2-quart oblong baking dish or 9-inch pie plate, arrange broccoli and chicken.
Combine soup, milk and melted cheese.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over soup mixture.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over bread crumbs.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend butter and cream cheese until softened.
Beat in sugar, one cup at a time, until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour continuously.
Bake at 350° in large tube pan.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork;
drain
fat.
Bring
4 cups water to a boil and add bouillon cubes.
Let dissolve.
Pour 2 cups broth over meat, reserving
2 cups.
Cook until meat is tender and liquid is absorbed.
For
the
sauce, add cornstarch, vinegar, brown sugar, soy
sauce
and pineapple juice to the reserved broth. Cook
until thick and bubbly.
Prepare Minute rice.
Add green peppers, onions and pineapple chunks to meat.
Stir-fry for 3 to 4
minutes until
tender.
Add
sauce and serve over rice. Add soy sauce to taste, if desired.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside. Cream margarine and Crisco. Add sugar and beat well. Add egg yolks, one at a time. Add vanilla. Sift flour and soda together and add, alternating with buttermilk, beating until smooth. Stir in coconut and nuts; fold in egg whites. Bake in 3 prepared layer pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry banana salad
directions: Cut bananas in halves and slice.
Drain pineapple juice into a medium bowl.
Set pineapple aside.
Add bananas to the juice. In large bowl, combine sugar and cranberry sauce.
Remove bananas. Discard juice.
Add bananas to cranberry mixture. Stir in pineapple, whipped topping and nuts.
Pour into a 13x9x2 inch dish.
Freeze until solid.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.
(Serves 16.)

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt
butter
with
sugar
and
dates.
When sugar dissolves, cook slowly 10 minutes.
Stir often.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Let cool.
Roll into small balls. Roll or shake
in
powdered sugar or coconut.
Makes 12 dozen balls. Keeps well in a tight container.
May be frozen.

title: soup in a pumpkin
directions: Cook minced onion in butter until tender but not browned; stir the bread crumbs into the onion and cook for 3 minutes.
Cut a cover out of the pumpkin; scrape out the inedible insides and rub the inside of the pumpkin and cover with soft butter.
Turn crumb mixture into the pumpkin; stir in Swiss cheese and fill to within 2 inches of top with chicken stock.
Season with salt, pepper and sage.

title: daddy's favorite macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Boil macaroni; drain.
In an 11 3/4 x 9 3/8 x 2 1/2-inch foil pan or large roaster, put 1/2 the cooked macaroni into bottom of pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cut up 1 stick of butter over the macaroni.
Add a layer of cheese. Repeat with the remaining half of the macaroni and other ingredients.
Before adding the final layer of cheese, add milk (enough to see rise on sides when macaroni is pushed down in center).
Add final layer of cheese.
Bake until cheese melts and browns.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat eggs well (use hand-held eggbeater).
Add the rest of the ingredients and beat until smooth.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto pregreased, preheated griddle.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Put brown and white sugar, butter and egg into a bowl and mix well.
Then add syrup, oatmeal, coconut and milk.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with a dollop of Cool Whip or whipped cream, if desired.

title: frito layered chili
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, place a layer of chili beans, tomato sauce and hamburger.
Next a layer of Fritos.
Next a layer of cheese. Repeat this one more time with each layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Melt together the chocolate and butter, then cool.
Mix sugar and eggs together, then add the chocolate and butter; add vanilla and flour.
Mix well, then add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Add cheese to hot white sauce, stir until melted and remove from medium heat. Add to beaten egg yolks gradually.
Add crab meat. Turn into casserole.
Mix butter and crumbs together. Garnish with crab meat claws and crumbs.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with sour milk. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets by teaspoons.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen.

title: stir-fry
directions: Put crushed bouillon cubes in medium saucepan.
Add hot water and let stand until dissolved.
Slice meat into thin strips.
Mix in bowl with soy sauce.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Divide meat and cook half at a time over medium heat until well browned.
Remove meat and add juices of first half to bouillon mixture.
(If meat is still firm, reduce heat and cover until tender.)
Let juices from second half of meat remain.
Add vegetables and more soy sauce to keep from sticking.
Quick fry on high.
Remove meat while still firm and bring to a boil.
Thicken with cornstarch.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
In a casserole dish, place a layer of Fritos, a layer of hamburger meat, sour cream, taco sauce and Mexican Velveeta.
Repeat order of layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: veg-bacon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Cut all 30 biscuits into quarters.
Dip each piece in the melted butter and layer, 1/3 at a time, into a Bundt or small angel food cake pan.
Sprinkle half of bacon, cheese, onion and green pepper.
Repeat layers, ending with biscuits.
Sprinkle top with any butter or cheese left over.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Clean and butter 6 large potatoes.
Prick the skins before baking.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Cut potatoes:
Slice lengthwise on top of each spud.
Carefully scoop out the insides.
Set aside shells.
Mash potatoes while hot.
Add butter, dairy sour cream (can use more) and boiled eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in chopped onion and English cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pile mashed potatoes in shells and sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and sour cream.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: cabbage-olive salad
directions: In large bowl mash the egg until well crumbled.
Blend in oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, pimento and onion.
Add cabbage and olives. Toss to mix.
Serve in lettuce cups.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Add pineapple, drained.
Add Cool Whip and pecans; mix well.
Pour into crusts. Let cool in refrigerator for at least 30 minutes and serve.

title: speedy stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from meat, reserving fat.
Cut meat in 1/4-inch thin strips, across grain.
Heat fat in skillet.
Remove trimmings when you have 3 tablespoons melted fat or add butter to make 3 tablespoons fat.
Quickly brown meat in the hot fat.
Add Worcestershire sauce and mushrooms.
Stir in soup mix and bring to a boil.
Blend sour cream and flour; stir in.
Cook and stir until heated through and slightly thick.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: pistollete rolls
directions: Brown meat, onions, bell pepper and seasonings.
Drain, add cheese and cooked broccoli.
Hollow out rolls and keep tops. Stuff rolls and put tops back on.
Brush tops with melted butter. Cook at 350° until brown.

title: rice krispy treats
directions: Melt margarine.
Add marshmallows.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Cook margarine and marshmallows over low heat until marshmallows are melted.
Add Rice Krispies and quickly stir together.
When well mixed, pour into a baking dish.
Using wax paper, flatten slightly in pan until top is smooth.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grate corn and add salt, pepper, sugar, flour and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: company scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until barely tender; cut in 1/2-inch slices. Saute mushrooms in butter. Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole and layer potatoes and mushrooms alternately. Heat soup, milk and onions; pour over potatoes. Sprinkle cheese and paprika over top. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Fold dry pudding into Cool Whip.
Add pineapples and juice, marshmallows and nuts.
Keep refrigerated until serving.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water. Drain. Cover beans and ham with 3 quarts of water. Add other ingredients and simmer at least 5 hours. Remove ham bone and cut meat into small pieces.
Return to soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Drain French-cut green beans and spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over beans.
Add rice, spreading evenly.
Add cooked, diced chicken.
Mix together the chicken broth and soups.
Pour over chicken in casserole.
Add seasonings from rice box.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Will serve 8.

title: gram's 10 egg cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla and nutmeg to taste (at least some of each).
Bake in angel cake pan at 350° for 1 hour, then lower oven temperature to 250° and continue baking for 1 hour more.
Freezes well if tightly wrapped.

title: chicken burgers
directions: Recipe has no eggs.

title: cornbread(serves 3 to 4)
directions: Mix ingredients and stir enough corn meal to make about like a thick gravy.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Combine in a bowl the sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Add flour and baking powder slowly, then add the nuts.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut while warm.

title: lazy rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast in the warm water, it needs to be quite warm. Place margarine, sugar and boiling water in a large bowl and stir until butter melts.
Cool until warm, add yeast mixture, egg, flour, salt and mix well.

title: royal roast beef
directions: Brown roast in butter and oil. Remove roast and brown onions. Remove pan from heat and add flour, stirring until blended.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and cook in crock-pot all day on low. Bone out chicken and pour broth in saucepan.
Mix soup with broth. Cut up tortillas and cook in broth mixture until done.
Add chicken.

title: pecan pie cookies
directions: Beat 1 cup butter and sugar at medium speed with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add 1/2 cup corn syrup and egg yolks, beating well. Gradually stir in flour; cover and chill 1 hour. Melt 1/4 cup butter in a heavy saucepan over medium heat; stir in powdered sugar and 3 tablespoons corn syrup. Cook, stirring often, until mixture boils. Remove from heat. Stir in pecans; chill 30 minutes. Shape mixture by 1/2 teaspoonfuls into 1/4-inch balls; set aside. Shape cookie dough into 1-inch balls; place 2-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheets. Beat egg whites until foamy; brush on dough balls. Bake at 375° for 6 minutes. Remove from oven and place pecan balls in center of each cookie. Bake 8 to 10 more minutes or until lightly browned. Cool 5 minutes on baking pans; remove to wire racks to cool completely. Freeze up to 1 month, if desired. Yield: 4 1/2 dozen.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake mix following directions on box, but make 3 layers. Let cool.
Thaw out Cool Whip and strawberries.
Mix Pet milk, jello and strawberries.
Place 1 layer of cake in a punch bowl. Punch holes all in the cake with a wooden spoon handle or something similar.
The more holes you punch, the better.
Spoon some of the strawberry mixture over the cake.
Layer over with Cool Whip. Repeat with layers 2 and 3. Refrigerate overnight.

title: zesty dressing
directions: In screw-top jar, combine all ingredients, except hard-cooked egg.
Cover and shake.
Chill.
Shake again just before serving. Stir in egg.
Makes about 1 cup dressing.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs lightly. Beat in both cheeses, flour, salt and pepper.
Drain broccoli well, patting dry with paper towels.
Stir into egg mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish, spreading evenly with a spoon.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until mixture is firm.
Loosen edges with spatula.
Slice and serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: "chicken enchilada pie"
directions: Reserve 2 cups corn chips for topping. Line a greased 12 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 2-inch casserole with remaining corn chips. Combine chicken, enchilada sauce, mushroom soup, onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Pour chicken mixture over chips. Pour chicken broth over entire mixture. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Top casserole with remaining chips, cheese and green chillies. Bake an additional 10 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In saucepan melt butter over low heat.
Put in bowl and add cocoa and stir until well blended.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour, vanilla and salt and stir just until mixed together.
Do not overbeat.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Spread in pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Boil potatoes until done, but not overcooked.
Put butter and cream in large bowl.
Add potatoes and mash until smooth.
Add salt to taste.
Add 1 1/2 cups Swiss cheese; mix well.
Put into large 9 x 13 pan.
Top with 1 1/2 cups Swiss cheese; sprinkle with plain bread crumbs (not too heavy). Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until top is nice and golden.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix cake mix with 1/3 cup evaporated milk and 3/4 cup melted margarine. Take half of the cake mixture and spread on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Melt caramels with remaining 1/3 cup milk. After cake mixture is baked, sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Spread the caramel mixture over top.
Drop remaining cake batter on top. Bake for an additional 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: rave review coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixer bowl.
Beat 4 minutes with mixer.
Stir in coconut and walnuts.

title: hawaiian supper
directions: Drain pineapple juice into measuring cup, add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir measured liquid, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch and salt in bowl.
Heat margarine in large skillet. Cook and stir ham, chicken, green pepper, scallions and garlic powder unti chicken is lightly browned.
Stir juice mixture to blend; pour into skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in pineapple and rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Chill well before serving.
This may sound easy and it is, but it is also delicious!

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 11 x 7 glass baking dish. Combine fruit, 1/2 c. sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil stirring frequently.
Keep mixture hot.
Meanwhile with spoon, beat egg, sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add milk. Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread batter in prepared pan. Pour hot fruit on top.
Bake 25-30 minutes.
Serve warm with cream.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate walnut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and Crisco together in double boiler over low heat.
When completely melted, stir in walnuts.
Remove from heat. Cover cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Drop mixture from tablespoon.
Let cool and harden.
Remove from paper.
Store in covered container.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix and let stand for several minutes.
In lightly greased skillet, add several tablespoons of batter to make round pattie.
Fry on each side until golden brown.
Serve with butter and syrup, also good with applesauce.
Can be doubled for larger servings.

title: sea leg salad
directions: Cook shell macaroni according to directions on box; drain, rinse with cold water to cool, drain again.
Chop or cut up Sea Leg, add to macaroni along with pimento, celery, green pepper, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Mix together well.
Season with black pepper.
No salt needed.

title: christmas morning egg casserole
directions: Cut crust of bread off and butter bread.
In greased casserole dish, put a layer of bread and a layer of cheese.
Repeat layers. Beat eggs, milk and seasoning and pour over bread.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet sour spareribs
directions: Marinate spareribs in salt, shoyu, cornstarch, garlic and ginger.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Fry spareribs in oil until golden brown.
Mix sugar, pineapple juice (*one small can is almost 1 cup of liquid; add enough water to make 1 cup) and vinegar in large pot.
Add cooked spareribs and simmer until tender (about 2 hours).
Add thickening made of 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water.
Arrange on platter and top with pineapple chunks.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until center springs back when touched.
Ice with your favorite frosting.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together and spread in a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chocolate truffle loaf
directions: Line a loaf pan with plastic.
Mix 1/2 cup cream with egg yolks.
In a 3-quart pan stir the chocolate, corn syrup and butter over a medium heat until melted.
Add egg mixture and stir constantly for 3 minutes.
Cool to room temperature and beat the remaining cream, sugar and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Fold into chocolate, pour into pan and freeze.
Unmold and slice thin. Serve with raspberry sauce.

title: cranberry nut coffee cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon. Set aside. Combine baking mix (biscuit), egg and water. Beat vigorously 1/2 minute.
Spread batter in greased square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with nut mix. Spoon cranberry sauce over the top. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°. While warm, spread with Confectioners Sugar Icing.

title: larry rameriz's quesadillas("like no others")
directions: Combine all ingredients (except cheese) in a bowl.
Add lukewarm water to make a soft dough.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in 2 x 2-inch squares.
Deep fry in hot fat until golden brown.
Dough will puff up.
Cut open at one end and fill with Cheddar or Jack cheese or a mix of both.
Heat in oven about 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve hot with red or green salsa.

title: creole chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with paprika and salt.
Brown chicken in butter in a skillet.
Add remaining ingredients except mushrooms. Simmer until chicken is tender.
Stir in mushrooms; simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: ouida's peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese. Beat in sugar and peanut butter. Slowly add milk. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into shell. Freeze until ready to serve.

title: southern baked ham
directions: Rinse ham and pat dry with paper towels. Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours. Put rack on lowest level of oven and preheat to 350°. Line large roasting pan with heavy foil. Place roasting rack in pan. Put ham on rack. Pour bourbon over ham and roast 2 hours. Mix 1/4 cup of the brown sugar with the spices, mustard, maple syrup and molasses. Remove ham from the oven and let cool for 1/2 hour. Cut away rind with scissors and trim the fat to 1/4-inch all over. Score the fat in a 1-inch diamond pattern. Brush with glaze. Pack brown sugar over glaze. Bake 1/2 hour. Brush dry spots with more bourbon. Bake 30 minutes. Let stand 30 minutes before carving. Makes 16 servings. (Six hours refrigerator to table.)

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions.
Cool and prick with fork.
Pour liqueur over cake.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Make mousse according to package directions.
Use less milk if using instant pudding.
Cut cake into cubes and put 1/2 into large glass bowl.
Layer 1/2 mousse, 1/2 Cool Whip and 1/2 candy on top.
Layer again (cake, mousse, Cool Whip and candy), then chill.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Combine with water in large pan, stirring until dissolved. Fold in strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Refrigerate for 1 1/2 hours or until firm.
Spread sour cream evenly over firm jello mix.
Spoon on remaining jello mixture gently, refrigerate.

title: old fashioned fried cabbage
directions: Add cabbage to melted butter in a large frying pan.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, adding salt and paprika after cabbage starts to simmer.
When cabbage is tender, not mushy, combine cream and vinegar.
Stir in gently.
Serve piping hot.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix together, chill and serve.

title: patato keftedes(potato balls)
directions: Mash the potatoes; add all the ingredients and mix well. Knead lightly.
With hands dusted a little with flour, roll the mixture into balls and then flatten them into rounds.
In a large frying pan, heat the oil and fry them until they are golden brown.

title: banana-pineapple dessert
directions: *You can use sugar-free instant pudding.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Save juice.
Slice cookies 1/4-inch thick and spread on greased pizza pan and pat together to make crust.
Bake as directed and cool.
Mix cheese, sugar and vanilla and spread on crust.
Spread pineapple on top of cheese.
Arrange on top of cheese.
Arrange fruit on crust in order listed.
Thicken juice with tapioca and let stand until cold.
Dribble on top of fruit and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Form into balls.
Melt 6 ounces semi-sweet chocolate chips with 1/2 bar paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate and dry on waxed paper.
Can be frozen or stored in cool location.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain. Put in bowl with everything else. Stir. Put in casserole dish. Cook 7 minutes on full power, then stir (use microwave). Cook 7 more minutes. Can be done the night before and then warmed up. Yield: 6 servings. Temperature: high. Time: 14 minutes.

title: apple cobbler cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then add flour, salt and soda.
Fold in chopped pecans and apples.
Pour into well greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in a preheated oven at 350°.

title: beasley's champion 1987 apple pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir together 4 cups unsifted flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt, mixing well.
Using a pastry blender, cut in lard until mixture is crumbly and particles are about the size of small peas.
Stir together egg, vinegar and 7 tablespoons ice water; mix well.
Pour egg mixture all at once into flour mixture.
Stir with a fork until it begins to clump together. Add remaining 1 tablespoon water, if needed, to make dough clump.

title: bean burgers
directions: Brown meat in pot and pour off grease.
Add beans and cook for 15 minutes.
Serve with tomatoes, onions and cornbread.
Serves 4.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water and simmer 10 minutes. Drain water into cup and use later.
(Try and have at least 3/4 cup, maybe 1 cup).

title: grammy's raisin cookies
directions: Boil water and raisins 5 minutes.
Cool.
Stir in soda.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add raisin mixture. Mix in sifted dry ingredients; add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: traditional venison sauce
directions: Pour oil in skillet and heat.
Saute carrot, onion and parsley about 5 minutes.
Add wine and simmer until reduced by half.
Add gravy and cook over low heat, about half an hour.
Strain.
Place in a saucepan and stir in cloves and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes. Serve over roasted or boiled venison.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix margarine, powdered sugar, graham crackers, vanilla and peanut butter together in large bowl.
Roll into balls (size of small walnuts).
Place toothpicks in each ball and refrigerate for 20 minutes.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs, butter flavoring and vanilla. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and melted German chocolate.
(Joy bakes hers in Bundt pan.)
Grease and flour pan or spray well with Pam.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool cake some in pan or turn out immediately.
This completely fills Bundt pan when baked.

title: kielbasa-n-sauce
directions: Slice kielbasa 1/4-inch thick.
Mix Durkee sauce and maple syrup in crock-pot.
Add kielbasa and heat on low for 3 to 4 hours, then serve.

title: breaded veal milan-style
directions: Unless the scaloppine are very small, cut them into pieces measuring about 3 x 3-inches or slightly larger.
Place them between sheets of wax paper and pound lightly to flatten, using the bottom of a heavy skillet or a flat mallet.
Season the flour with salt and pepper.
Beat the egg with the water, the 1/2 teaspoon of oil and nutmeg.
Blend the bread crumbs with Parmesan.
Dip the scaloppine on both sides first in flour, then in egg and finally in the bread crumb mixture.
As the scaloppine are breaded, place them on a flat surface and tap lightly to help the bread crumbs adhere. Heat the butter and remaining oil in a heavy skillet and add the scaloppine.
Cook until golden brown on one side, 2 to 4 minutes. Cook until golden brown on the other side.
Serve hot with sliced lemon.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: spinach squares
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add beaten eggs, milk and melted butter, then stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly around edges.
When cool, cut into squares and freeze on cookie sheets, then bag.
When serving, heat squares 20 minutes at 350° until brown on edges.

title: crab canapes
directions: Melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Split muffins. Spread mixture on muffins.
Freeze 1 hour.
Cut each half in 6 pieces.
Broil 5 to 6 minutes.

title: peanutty chewy bars(makes 24 to 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, stir together flour, granulated sugar, cocoa, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add eggs; mix well.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and top evenly with chips, then sweetened condensed milk and coconut.
Return to oven; bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.
Garnish with Drizzle.
Cut into bars.
Store covered at room temperature.

title: nurses cookies
directions: Measure 5 cups of oatmeal and blend in blender until oatmeal is a fine powder.
Then continue with the recipe.
This recipe makes 112 cookies.
You may need to cut the recipe in half.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Put nuts in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put coconut on top of nuts.
Mix cake mix as directed on box and pour on top of nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese and margarine on low heat until mixed. Stir in confectioners sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over batter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut heat to 325° if using Pyrex dish.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into balls, size of walnut.
Place on cookie sheet, 2-inches apart, crisscross with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients well with a wire whisk
for at least 5 minutes. Chill. Refrigerate unused portion. Good with chicken nuggets.

title: healthy cookies(great for diabetics)
directions: Mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large saucepot.
Stir in bouillon cubes, split peas, onion, carrots, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for about 5 hours.
For thicker soup, cook longer.
Each serving contains 140 calories.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Melt margarine and beat with cake mix and 1 egg. Press into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat cream cheese, other 3 eggs and sugar together.
Pour on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese.
Add to broccoli and mix together.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Top with cheese crackers crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased pan and bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut bacon in mushroom-size squares.
Remove and chop mushroom stems to make 1/2 cup.
Set caps aside.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown pork chops in fat.
Remove chops from the skillet and then mix 2 1/2 cups of water with the onion soup mix in the same skillet.
Put rice and bell pepper in a 2-quart casserole.
Lay pork chops on top of rice and pour soup mixture over the chops. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until transparent, not brown.
Add rice to water and cook 5 minutes.
Place rice, onions and cheese in baking dish.
Stir in half and half.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix chili
and	cheese	until all cheese is melted, add picante sauce.
Put
in
bowl and put sour cream in center and then sprinkle with tomatoes, onions and avocado.

title: chocolate frosting 1
directions: Combine ingredients, melt slowly, boil 5 minutes or to soft ball.
Cool and beat.
Add vanilla and beat again with spoon. Spread on cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine
butter,
sugar
and
corn syrup; cook over low heat until
sugar
is dissolved.
Cool; add eggs, vanilla and salt. Mix
well.	Place
in pie shell.
Top with pecan halves and bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Stir flour into sugar.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake one hour or longer.
Start oven at 400°, then turn the oven to about 200° or 300°.

title: cheese petit fours
directions: *Bread:
Discard heels and trim crusts using bread or electric knife.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease shallow baking dish.
Brown chops in greased frying pan.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with celery, brown sugar, lemon juice and seasonings.
Pour tomato sauce and water over chops.
Cover and bake in moderate 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours until chops are done.
Serves 4.

title: baked mexican eggs
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add flour and baking powder.
Blend.
Melt butter; add to eggs along with chilies and cheeses (and ham). Blend gently.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Add small amount of bacon grease.
Mix together and let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Mix juice with flour and egg.
Cook until thick, stirring frequently (do this in the microwave).

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Meanwhile, mix well all other ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Add noodles to tuna mixture; mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish; top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: raspberry dumplings
directions: Boil water, sugar and raspberries.
Mix all the dry ingredients.
Mix the butter with the dry ingredients until blended.
Beat the egg with the milk and incorporate all at once to the dry ingredients.
Don't overbeat the dough.
Add teaspoonful of the dough in the raspberries syrup.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
You can use strawberries or blueberries, if you prefer.

title: snicker bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in double boiler or microwave 3 minutes. In large bowl, mix melted margarine, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and cake mix. Press half of cake mix into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate pieces. Cover with melted caramels. Dot top with remaining cake mix. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Refrigerate; pull out to room temperature to cut.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix broken pretzels and put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Heat the margarine until melted; pour over pretzels. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°, stirring twice.
Let cool.

title: orange blossom crepes
directions: In small mixing bowl mix cheese with milk and almond extract. Add finely chopped almonds.
Spread onto center of crepe (crepes must be thin, or they will split).
Roll up and set aside.
In large skillet or chafing dish, melt butter.
Stir in sugar and lemon juice.
Dissolve cornstarch in orange juice.
Add orange juice mixture, orange liqueur and grated peel to butter.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly until thick and translucent.
Put filled crepes in skillet or chafing dish of hot orange sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Pour warm cognac over all.
Ignite with long match. Spoon flaming sauce over crepes.
Garnish each with toasted almonds.
Serve with dessert coffee or Espresso.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cook peaches with sugar, vanilla and butter until melted.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour into peaches.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 300° until done.

title: 1-2-3 crock-pot dinner
directions: Set crock-pot on low at 9 to 10 a.m. for sit down dinner for 4 persons at 6 to 7 p.m.
Drop beef chunks (bite size) into crock-pot.
Chop onion and add to beef.
Mix soup and water with everything; stir.
Let cook 6 to 9 hours.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Melt butter or oleo and minced garlic.
Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken in butter mixture, then roll in dry mixture.
Place rolled chicken in casserole pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: linzer torte
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add the flour, lemon rind and the nuts.
Knead for thirty minutes.
Break off three-quarters of the dough and roll into a round about nine inches across and one inch high.
Take a plate which is about eight inches across and press into the round until
you have an indentation of about half an inch.
Put the pastry in a flan tin, and spread it evenly with the jam.
Roll out the remaining pastry thinly, and cut into strips.
Weave the strips of pastry across the top to form a lattice.
Bake in a medium oven for one hour.

title: nettie pearl's ground nut candy
directions: In heavy pan, combine syrup, sugar and butter.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Add ground peanuts and cook for 15 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Form into little cakes on buttered cookie sheet and let harden.

title: cheese bake potatoes
directions: Slice raw potatoes and onion; cook until done.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Pour over cooked potatoes.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: spinach noodles
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and salt at medium speed with electric mixer until blended.
With spoon, stir in Ricotta, noodles and spinach.
Turn into buttered baking dish.
Mix butter with bread crumbs; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° until a knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburg and onions.
Drain grease and add beans, simmer for 5 minutes.
In large serving bowl, arrange lettuce, tomato, olives, chips and cheese.
Pour hot hamburger mixture over salad and toss quickly.

title: layered chicken salad
directions: In medium bowl, layer 1/2 each of the following ingredients in this order:
cooked chicken, water chestnuts, alfalfa sprouts and onion rings.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the dressing and 1/2 of the pepper.
Repeat layers and sprinkle with remaining dressing and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve cold. Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, cream peanut butter, shortening, 1/3 cup sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda; gradually add to creamed mixture, blending thoroughly.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.

title: spice tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Can store mixture in covered jar indefinitely.
Use 1 teaspoon of mixture per cup of hot water.

title: tuna noodles hot dish
directions: Make a medium sauce of first three ingredients.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Then fold in the rest of ingredients. Bake 30 minutes at 350.
Before baking, I put finely crushed potato chips on top of the casserole.

title: sweet and sour vegetable soup
directions: Put hamburger, bacon and onion in a soup pot and cook until brown.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook until everything is heated thoroughly.
(If the soup seems too thick, you may add some water, but only about 1/2 cup at a time.)

title: yam cake
directions: Resift flour with salt and soda, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg. In mixing bowl, combine sugar and cooking oil; mix thoroughly. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Add dry ingredients and mashed yams, pecans and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly. Put into greased tube pan and bake in moderate oven at 350°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool.
Slit cake horizontally and spread filling between sections.

title: a touch of mexico casserole
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and celery in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave at High for 7 minutes, or until meat is done.
Stir several times while cooking; drain.
Stir in next 7 ingredients; microwave at High for 5 to 6 minutes, turning dish a half turn after 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and corn chips.
Microwave at 70% power for 1 minute, or until cheese melts. Yields 6 servings.

title: "frozen fruit salad"
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover with foil and freeze. Set out 5 hours before serving.

title: apricot spice cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add baby food one jar at a time.
Add half of flour blended with spices, salt and baking powder, then beat in remainder of flour. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and floured tube pan.
Let cool, right side up.
Turn cake out onto cake plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: birds nests
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add yolks and flour.
Make small balls.
Dip into egg whites.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Take out. Press with thumb in middle.
Put back into oven for 10 more minutes.
Fill middle with raspberry jam.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homestead cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Place cornmeal in mixing bowl.
Add milk, egg and melted shortening or oil.
Stir only enough to thoroughly mix ingredients. Pour immediately into well-greased 6-inch square pan and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Sift cocoa, sugar and flour together in bowl.
In saucepan, bring water, oleo and oil to boil.
Pour over dry ingredients in bowl and beat until creamy.
Add buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake in a greased jelly roll pan at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, put a layer of potatoes, salt and pepper.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and milk in a bowl.
Put mushroom mixture on top of potatoes, then a layer of cheese.
Repeat process.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or so.

title: chicken-veggie soup
directions: The purchase weight of 10 pounds of chicken decreases after boiling and removing bones, skin and fat.
Chop all vegetables. Boil all ingredients in at least 1 gallon of water. Add more water, if necessary.
Boil for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well.
Add the flour. Stir until mixed well. Roll walnut size balls and place on cookie sheet.
Use floured fork to flatten cookies down.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Add juice and water.
Heat to boiling and dissolve jello in hot liquid.
Cool until syrupy. With fork, mix cranberry sauce and drained pineapple.
Add to jello.
Turn in glass dish.
Refrigerate until it sets up a little, about 15 minutes.

title: broiled chicken and vegetable kabobs
directions: Trim ends off and cut zucchini crosswise into 1-inch slices. Trim ends off stems of mushrooms.
In plastic food storage bag, place zucchini and mushrooms.
Cut boned chicken into 1 1/4-inch chunks.
Add chicken and salad dressing to vegetables in bag. Seal; shake carefully to coat mixture with dressing.
Refrigerate 1 hour to marinate.
Meanwhile, soak 8 (12-inch) bamboo skewers in water.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Let stand until oats absorb the moisture.
Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Each cookie has 90 calories.

title: spring salad
directions: Heat applesauce until very hot and bubbling.
Dissolve Jell-O into it.
Let mixture cool.
Add 7-Up.
Stir and pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill overnight.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and oil.
Mix well and add blueberries.
Pour in muffin tins and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: smoked fish pate
directions: Shred fish very fine (can use food processor). Blend into remaining ingredients until smooth. Serve with crackers or take loaf of unsliced rye bread. Scoop out center in bite size pieces; put pate in center and place pieces around loaf.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Note:
Chicken breast may need to be pounded into thinner pieces.

title: chili with potatoes
directions: Heat
heavy
4-quart
pot.
Drop
meat
in.
When
meat begins to
brown on the bottom, add garlic, onion, celery and bell pepper.
Stir
with meat until well sauteed.
Add tomato sauce, bay
leaf
and
stir until boiling.
Add chili powder, salt, pepper
and
cups
of
water (or beef stock made from cooking soup bones).
Bring to boil, then simmer for about 30 minutes. Add potatoes and parsley, cook 30 more minutes until potatoes are tender.
Seasoning and water may be added according
to
taste. Serve
hot
with
slices
of
Cheddar cheese, crackers and homemade bread.

title: veggie wedges
directions: Press rolls into ungreased jelly roll pan; cover bottom of pan and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Hidden Valley Ranch dressing and Miracle Whip with mixer.
Spread over rolls.
Mix vegetables all together.
Sprinkle over top of cheese mixture.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cool at least 3 to 4 hours.
Cut into small pieces or squares.

title: cream of garlic soup
directions: In large pot, combine ham, onion, garlic and potatoes.
Add butter and oil.
Saut until onions are tender and potatoes are cooked.
Add chicken broth.
Puree in small batches and return to pot.
Blend in cream and half and half.
Heat through but do not boil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 6.

title: *chicken oregano
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine oregano, salt and pepper in small dish. Rub this mixture into chicken pieces. Arrange in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Blend together the olive oil and lemon juice. Pour over chicken pieces and bake for 40 minutes until tender.

title: beat 'n eat(white frosting)
directions: Mix ingredients (except water) in a small, deep bowl.
Add boiling water; beat until stiff.
This recipe makes a fluffy frosting that will stay moist for 2 or 3 days.

title: our first annual super bowl party chili
directions: In large stockpot brown ground beef, drain.
Add green pepper and onions.
Cook until onions are clear.
Salt and pepper.
Add seasoning mix, water, tomatoes and beans.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, during first half of game (or about 45 to 60 minutes).
Garnish with shredded cheese; add chili powder, if desired.
Use Resolve carpet cleaner for spills.
Double the recipe to serve 12 hungry teens at a Super Bowl party!

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given and drop by spoonfuls.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, cut in bite size pieces.
Finely crumble bread and mix with chicken.
Mix flour in fat in skillet, mix well.
Put broth in and bring to a boil to thicken.
Add celery and onions. Pour over chicken and bread, mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
May be served hot or cold.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Melt together the semi-sweet bits and Eagle Brand milk in double boiler or heavy saucepan.
When melted, add the remaining ingredients.
Pour in pan and let cool.

title: happiness pie
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in saucepan. Bring to full boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cream cheese and stir until smooth. Add vanilla.
Let mixture cool for 5 minutes, stirring twice. Pour pudding mixture into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Place strawberries in circle around outer edge of pie.
Put 1 large strawberry in center of pie. Place blueberries over remaining pudding surface.
Serve with whipped cream or other topping, if desired.

title: monkey bread
directions: Prepare a Bundt pan.
Grease with butter or oleo.
Coat with chopped pecans.

title: date oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the first 5 ingredients.
Sift together and stir in the next 3 ingredients.
Stir in oats, dates and nuts.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls size of large walnuts. Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet; flatten (to 1/4-inch) with bottom of glass dipped in flour.
Bake until lightly browned at 375°.
Bake 10 to 12
minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Blend ingredients for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased tube or bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan.
