Remove cake from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken or tuna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter bottom of casserole dish and sprinkle onion and celery in bottom.
Bake until soft.
In separate bowl, add all the other ingredients except potato chips. Spoon on top of onion and celery mixture.
Sprinkle with crushed potato chips; dot with butter and put paprika on top.

title: apfelkuchen met gub(apple custard cake)
directions: Beat margarine and sugar well. Add cinnamon and blend in flour.
Divide dough in half.
Press half into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Add egg to other half and mix well.

title: summer garden vegetable medley
directions: Prepare all vegetables and drain.
Place butter and vegetables in a large skillet.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Cover and steam cook 12 minutes, until just tender-crisp.
Stir in cheese and croutons.
Serve at once.

title: marinated tomatoes and cucumbers
directions: In a 2-quart shallow baking dish arrange tomatoes, cucumbers and onion.

title: mom's peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook water and sugar to a rolling boil; check the doneness of the syrup by putting small amount into cold bowl of water.
If syrup balls up...it is done!

title: crab melt-aways
directions: Mix all ingredients except muffins. Spread on open muffins and place in freezer for at least 30 minutes. Cut each open-faced muffin into fourths (this will make them bite sized). Broil for 5 minutes or until golden brown. You may also prepare these weeks ahead of time and freeze until ready to use - then just pull out of the freezer and broil!

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except barbecue sauce.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Spoon mixture into casserole.
Spread barbecue sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Remove from oven and let set for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Put oil in black iron skillet.
Turn to medium heat.
Salt and pepper chicken pieces.
Roll in flour.
Put in skillet.
Lightly brown on one side.
Turn chicken.
Put lid on pan.
Turn down heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Take lid off of chicken; turn up heat and brown chicken golden brown, turning chicken often.
Chicken will be good and done when deep golden brown.

title: baked fish au gratin
directions: Place half of the fillets in greased baking dish and cover with 4 slices of cheese.
Sprinkle with thyme and parsley.
Saute onions and add.
In top of double boiler, melt butter; stir in flour.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until the mixture thickens.
Pour over fish and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: onion rye appetizers
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine the crushed fried onions, bacon bits, mayonnaise and Swiss cheese. Stir well. Spread about 1 teaspoon pizza sauce on each slice of party rye.
Top with about 1 tablespoon cheese mixture.

title: sadithe
directions: Make the night before.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together and bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool thoroughly.

title: roquefort ranch dressing
directions: Combine sour cream and mayonnaise.
Crumble up the Roquefort cheese into the mixture and blend.
Store in closed container. Refrigerate.

title: full-meat casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Salt and pepper to taste as you put ingredients together.
Use a pan deeper than a skillet (easier to mix together).
Add onion.
Add everything else except cheese and macaroni.
Then add 2 cups of the cheese.
Drain macaroni (do not rinse) and add to mixture.
Put all in casserole dish.
Add last cup of cheese to top of mixture.
Add tomato wedges on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until mixture bubbles. Cover with foil, then remove to melt cheese.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix milk, soda, cream, sugar, butter and shortening.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well.
Then add milk and flour.
Add vanilla; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add coconut and nuts. Bake in 2 layers pans, greased and floured, at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer spinach, lettuce, egg slices, onions and peas.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and Worcestershire sauce together and spread over salad.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Cover and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: ice cream sandwich(lighter eating - 3 points)
directions: Allow the cool whip to soften so that it can be spread between the crackers to about the thickness of a typical ice cream sandwich. Re-freeze and enjoy!

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Toss sugar, flour and corn meal with fork.
Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake for 25 additional minutes.

title: easy okra gumbo
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic until done.
Mash up tomatoes until soupy.
Put in large pot.
Add water with this until pot is almost full.
Leave room for meat and okra.
Let this cook to a boil, then simmer.
Put okra in skillet with 3 tablespoons oil and brown until okra is no longer sticky.
Add with what you already have cooking.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add over cooked rice. Salt and pepper to your taste while cooking.
It's ready (eat).

title: dirt
directions: Crush Oreos.
Make pudding according to package.
Add cream cheese and last, Cool Whip.
Alternate Oreos and pudding, making last layer Oreos.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and form meatballs.
Brown in butter.
Heat jelly and catsup until blended.
Add browned meatballs and simmer 25 minutes.
If you make the day before, then heat next day, they are better.

title: sweet corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass pan. Blend all ingredients in a food processor until nearly smooth. Pour into prepared dish. Bake until brown and the center is set, about 45 minutes. Cool 10 minutes and serve.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and
cut pieces from bone (or use boneless chicken breasts).
Melt
butter
and
keep
in
separate bowl. Crush one roll of
Ritz
crackers
and press in bottom of pan. Pour 1/2 of
the
butter
mixture
over
the crushed crackers. Break up the chicken pieces
and layer them in the dish on top of cracker crumbs.
Mix
sour cream and soup; pour over chicken. Crush next
roll
of
crackers
and
sprinkle
over
soup mixture. Pour remainder
of margarine over the top.
Sprinkle top with poppy seed.
Bake
for 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until bubbly. Serves 4 to 6.

title: soy grits loaf
directions: Cook grits with salt in boiling water until dry.
Run crumbs and onion through food chopper.
Add to cooked grits with seasoning, beaten eggs and milk.
Mix well.

title: kisses
directions: Beat egg white until frothy.
Stir in sugar then add pecans. Pick up with hands in small balls.
Mash down a little and place on pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or 325° for 10 or 12 minutes.
Cool 3 or 4 minutes before removing from pan. Makes about 45.

title: west coast casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour, mustard, Worcestershire, paprika and milk.
Cook, stirring until thick and smooth.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Remove from heat; add 1/2 cup olives (sliced and drained), shrimp and crab.
Bake in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole for 25 minutes at 350° or until bubbly. Garnish top with remaining olives and parsley.
Serves 5 to 6. Good with buttered rice.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar on low with the mixer and then add drained pineapple and mix together.
Spread mixture on ham slices and roll up.
Wrap in plastic wrap and freeze.
When ready to serve, cut rolls into slices.
Serve on small rounds of bread or crackers.

title: baked apple(microwave)
directions: Put cored apple in microwave dish.
Sprinkle with apple pie spice and sugar as desired in core.
Bake in microwave oven on High for about 1 1/2 minutes or until soft.

title: m&m's chocolate oatmeal chews(stacks)
directions: Combine the first four ingredients (sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk) and cook on eye of stove on medium heat until thick. Remove from the heat and stir in quick oatmeal and salt.
Add vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: butter "stuff"(herb butter)
directions: *Bread Baking Hint:
When baking French, sourdough, etc., bread, put bread on the racks in oven uncovered.
Fill a cup with about 1/4 cup water.
Throw water onto bottom of oven (avoiding the bread) and close oven door quickly.
This will give the bread a crunchier crust.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cook ground beef; stir in sauce and seasonings.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In a bowl, combine 1 cup Mozzarella, sour cream and eggs; stir in spaghetti.
Place mixture in a 9 x 13 baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese. Spread meat sauce mixture over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until heated through.
Uncover and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: red beans and rice
directions: *If fresh herbs are unavailable, Italian seasoning may be substituted.

title: chocolate cake(10 small layers)
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs, part of flour, then milk and rest of flour and vanilla.
Cook each layer at 350° until done.

title: waffles "sinless"
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into hot waffle iron.
(Spray with butter flavor Pam first.)

title: cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, cream the cheese until smooth.
Gradually stir in crushed pineapple, green pepper, onion and salt.
Shape into ball and wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
To serve, place cheese ball on board and serve with assorted crackers.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix and serve with chips.

title: pea soup
directions: If you don't have a ham bone, use leftover smoked butt.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage in a medium skillet until browned and then drain. Set aside.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add beaten eggs, cheese, milk, salt, mustard, pepper and bread.
Beat with an eggbeater.
Pour in casserole dish, cover and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
May be frozen.
Great for breakfast or brunch.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O according to box directions.
Set Jell-O until cold, not firm.
Mix cream, after whipped with Jell-O and sugar. Mix all well and add fruit and cheese.
Stir all together and pour into pan or bowl; let set.

title: light spaghetti salad
directions: Put seasoning mix, chopped cucumbers, tomatoes and salad dressing in large bowl and mix.
Cook spaghetti noodles, drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine noodles with ingredients in bowl and let sit overnight.

title: chocolate fudge meringues
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt to soft peaks in medium bowl.
Beat to stiff peaks, adding sugar gradually.
Fold in cocoa, then fold in chopped chocolate.
Drop mixture by tablespoons onto aluminum foil-lined cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° until cookies feel crisp when touched (20 to 25 minutes).
Cool on pans on wire racks.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Sift together flour, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and soda.
Add flour mixture to first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: elizabeth young's ham loaf
directions: Grind together ham and pork.
Mix all ingredients together (except raisins) very well.
Cover bottom of 2 loaf pans with raisins, then add pork and ham mixture.
Set pans in larger pan to which you have added some water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours plus.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: broccoli - corn bake
directions: Combine ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: mixed berry syrup
directions: Heat raspberry jam, butter and water in saucepan until hot. Add blueberries and heat a little more. Serve warm.

title: hamburger and green bean casserole
directions: Mix together browned and drained hamburger, onion, cheese, green beans and mushroom soup.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour all ingredients into blender. Blend on high for 1 minute or mix by hand until smooth.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender in 5 to 6 cups water; drain.
Remove from bones and cube.
Crush tortilla chips and spread in a 2-quart casserole.
Add chicken.
Blend remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and boiling water.
Stir until sugar dissolves. Add lemon juice and cold water.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: marinated tomato and cucumber salad
directions: Combine tomato wedges, cucumber slices and onion rings in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine vinegar, vegetable oil, mayonnaise, sugar and salt.
Beat, using a wire whisk, until smooth.
Pour dressing over tomato mixture, tossing gently.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with a slotted spoon.

title: texas onion bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Saute onions in butter.
Mix with biscuit mix, milk, egg and 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into greased 8-inch baking pan.
Top with remaining cheese and poppy seed. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken breasts on rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the soup and milk; reserve 1/2 cup.
Mix soup with rice, mushrooms and half the onion soup mix.
Pour into large baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Pour reserved soup on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover; bake for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package. Drain and put aside.
Chop and cook the onion in 1/3 stick butter or margarine until clear.
Add Cheez Whiz, Minute rice, soup and drained broccoli to onion. Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes (covered).

title: orange chocolate chip bread(16 servings)
directions: Combine milk, orange juice, sugar, egg and orange peel in small bowl; stir into baking mix in a medium mixing bowl.
Beat until well combined, about 1 minute.
Stir in chocolate chips. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Slice and serve.
Store leftovers in foil or plastic wrap.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until done.
One cup equals 2 vegetables.

title: stephanie's cheese wrapped grapes
directions: You will need a jellyroll pan about 11 x 17-inches, lined with parchment paper.

title: island teriyaki
directions: Slice steak in 1/4-inch wide strips while still frozen. Marinate in mixture of soy sauce, brown sugar, olive oil, ginger, pepper and garlic.
Leave overnight in refrigerator.
Put on bamboo skewers, weaving meat every 2 inches.
Put on barbecue. Cook to taste.

title: eggs florentine
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise.
Mash yolks.
Mix in vinegar, mustard, mayonnaise or salad dressing, Worcestershire, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and milk.
Fill egg whites with mixture.

title: merry cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients (except whipped cream) well.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: country green beans
directions: In a sauce pan, combine all ingredients. Cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes or until beans are crisp-tender.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients until dissolved.
Let cool.
Put in refrigerator until thick.
Whip until fluffy.
Add Cool Whip.
Put in pretty glass dish and decorate with mandarin oranges.
Serves 8.

title: black midnight cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Throw all in blender and mix.
Brush pie crust with butter and chill while mixing.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla, salt and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg; beat until blended.
Gradually stir in milk; mix well.
Pour into baked, cooled pie shell.
Sprinkle with additional nutmeg if desired.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake an additional 35 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature before serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add coconut and chopped pecans.

Cook until golden brown, stirring frequently. Set aside and let cool. Combine cream cheese, condensed milk and beat until smooth. Fold in whipped topping. Layer 1/4 cream cheese mixture in each pie shell. Drizzle 1/4 of caramel topping on each pie. Sprinkle 1/4 coconut mixture evenly over each pie. Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Cover and freeze. Let stand 3 to 4 minutes before slicing.

title: favorite cheese balls
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients.
Add the next 3 ingredients and mix well.
Divide into 3 balls and roll in chopped walnuts or pecans.
Wrap well in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate a few hours. Yields 3 balls.

title: hummus
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in food processor.
When it's like a spread, taste it and add salt and pepper.
Add 1/4 cup water to the spread; taste again, add tahini.
Serve the Humus on a plate.
Put olive oil in the middle, paprika and a leaf of parsley for decoration.
Dip pieces of pita bread in Humus.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: ham rolls
directions: Remove	rolls
from
foil
in package.	Do not separate rolls. Slice rolls in half and return bottom of rolls back to foil from package.
Mix first 5 ingredients together and pour over bottom part
of
rolls.
Top
with
the
chopped ham and grated Swiss cheese.
Put tops of rolls back on top of cheese and heat, uncovered,	for
to
12 minutes in a 350° oven. Serve warm! Very good.

title: banana split pie
directions: Cook until thick; use any kind of pie shell desired.
Line pie shell with bananas first, then a layer of pineapple, then a layer of nuts.
Top with Cool Whip or Dream Whip, sprinkling with coconut.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Blend, stir or squeeze tomatoes into small pieces.
Put in a pot and simmer.
Add butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Crumble bread into small pieces.
Stir in tomatoes until mixture is very moist and very thick.
Butter pan and pour mixture into it.
Bake at 350° to 400° until firm and top is slightly brown.
(Leftover biscuits may be used in place of loaf bread.)

title: broccoli and ham casserole
directions: Fix au gratin potatoes according to the package and put into cake pan.
Slice ham into small pieces and add to potatoes. Defrost broccoli and add to potatoes and ham.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: russian salad
directions: Place Jell-O, water, cheese and marshmallows in large boiler and cook until dissolved.
Remove from heat and add pineapple, nuts, milk, mayonnaise and banana.
Pour into dish and place in refrigerator until congealed.

title: fudge
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Stir in milk; bring to a boil (bubbly), boiling over medium heat, stirring, until soft ball stage or reaches 230°.
Remove from fire and add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature or 110°.
Beat until thickens and loses gloss.
Spread in lightly buttered pan.
Let cool.
Cut and serve.

title: apple crunch
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Meanwhile, peel, core and thinly slice the apples.
Combine apple or orange juice, the brown sugar and the cornstarch.
Toss the apples.
Place apple mixture in a 1-quart casserole.
Cover and bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are very tender.
Sprinkle the granola over the apples just before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add egg and coconut extract.
Beat well.
Shape dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Arrange 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 14 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: bread sticks
directions: Cut hot dog buns into strips.
Put on cookie sheet.
Put butter and Salad Supreme on and bake at 200° for 1 hour.

title: potato burgers
directions: Mix onion and potatoes.
Add salt and hamburger.
Mix well; shape into patties.
Brown on one side in a heavy skillet.
Turn; pour tomatoes over patties.
Cover.
Continue cooking on low heat for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil together until well blended.
Stir in dry ingredients and fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar if desired.
Do not grease or flour pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash and add onion, soup, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Butter casserole dish generously and sprinkle layer of crumb mixture on bottom.
Add squash mixture and top with crumb mixture and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake
at
315° for 10 minutes; lower oven to 300°.
Bake about 1 hour or until done.	Makes 2 large loaves or 3 medium.

title: szechwan chicken
directions: Cut chicken 1-inch size.
In a small bowl stir together teriyaki sauce, stir-fry sauce and cornstarch.
Set aside.

title: potato-sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
In large casserole, layer potatoes, soup mixture and sausage.
Repeat layer again, ending with sausage.
Dot with butter.
Bake, covered, at 350°
for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle with grated cheese and melt in oven.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the sugar and milk.
Sift 1/2 of the flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to the egg mixture. Beat the batter with mixer until smooth, adding as much flour as needed.
Batter should be thin enough to pour.

title: cold lagoon chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Refrigerate at least 30 minutes. Gets better the longer it sits. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: moist coconut filling
directions: Mix sugar and milk in a saucepan and boil until it becomes a syrup.
Add coconut and cook 2 or 3 minutes more.
Spread on cake layers.

title: danish potato salad
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt, pepper and mustard in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; gradually beat in well-beaten eggs.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened, for about 5 minutes.
Beat in salad dressing. Toss together potatoes, hard-cooked eggs, cucumber, onion and green pepper.
Pour on dressing; toss gently.
Adjust seasoning if necessary.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana popsicles
directions: Peel bananas and place a stick in it.
Dip it in orange juice and then roll it in nuts.
Freeze and eat.

title: hot scotchie
directions: Into each of 4 mugs, place 2 tablespoons butterscotch pieces. Heat at High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
For each drink, stir into 1 cup milk and dash ground cinnamon.
Heat at Medium 6 to 7 minutes. Stir in marshmallows.
Heat at Medium 3/4 to 1 minute.
Yields 4 servings (8 ounces each).

title: shrimp and tortellini
directions: Cook pasta.
Melt butter, add shrimp, shallot and basil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add pasta and cheese.
Toss. Serves 4.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine nuts, dates, baking soda and salt in a bowl.
Add shortening and water.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs slightly; add vanilla.
Stir in the sugar and flour.
Add to date mixture.
Do not overmix.
Place in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool before slicing.

title: squash brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter, oil and sugars.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
In separate bowl, combine dry ingredients, then gradually stir
dry ingredients into liquid mixture.
Stir in grated squash.
Pour batter into greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate morsels.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; roll into balls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Mix together ketchup, brown sugar, water, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat until thickened. Put meatballs in crock-pot; pour mixture over meatballs and simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: quick and easy quiche
directions: Sprinkle ham into 9-inch pie plate.
Combine baking mix, butter, milk, eggs, salt and pepper in blender container; process until smooth.
Pour over ham.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for several minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: refrigerator chocolate cake
directions: Alternate layers of cookies and cream, starting with cookies on the bottom and cream on top.
Also, crumble mashed cookies on top to finish.
Needs to be stored overnight in refrigerator before serving.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mom's apple slices
directions: Sift together flour, salt.
Add shortening.
Beat egg, egg yolk, water and lemon juice, add to flour mixture.
Set aside.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring water and margarine to boil.
Stir in flour and stir vigorously until ball forms.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Spread in large, ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 400° oven until puffed and golden.
Prick bubbles with fork.
Cool away from draft.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cook pudding according to directions on package.
Pour hot pudding into dry cake mix and beat until thoroughly mixed.
Pour batter into cake pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and walnuts.
Bake at 350° approximately 35 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and cut up.
Fry bacon, then cook sliced onions in bacon grease.
Drain; add onions and bacon to potatoes.
Heat up salad dressing and pour over potatoes.
Mix and serve.

title: zesty meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for
1 hour.

title: chuckwagon soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions. Stir in taco seasoning mix, then add other ingredients; bring to a boil, then let simmer for a couple of hours. Stir occasionally.

title: praline cheese dessert
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and oleo and press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine softened cream cheese, brown sugar and flour; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Pour mixture over crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted 1 inch from the edge comes out clean.
Chill.
Cut into 20 to 25 servings.
Delicious but rich.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix chocolate, cake mix, eggs, oil, water and pudding.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Mix in sour cream; add chocolate chips and nuts. Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick and easy cookies
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil, water and eggs.
To this mixture, add any of the following:
chocolate chips or M&M's or raisins. Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let them cool for 1 minute and remove from pan. Makes 3 dozen.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Coarsely chop peppers, onions, celery and garlic.
Saute in hot grease until tender.
Add shrimp.
Cook slowly until pink.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend soup, milk and cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in small skillet.
Pour in bread crumbs.
Stir until brown.
Sprinkle crumbs over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken potato corn chowder
directions: In large saucepan, stir all ingredients until well blended. Bring to boil over medium heat.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 4 servings; contains 281 calories per serving.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Place beans in dish; top with ham or chicken.
In saucepan, combine soup, milk and cheese and pepper to taste.
Cook over medium heat until thick; pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sandy's eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding and milk until thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip. Line bottom of pan (9 x 13-inch) with graham crackers.
Cover with half of pudding mix.
Layer graham crackers and the rest of pudding and another layer of graham crackers.

title: ecumenical luncheon punch
directions: Combine liquids.
Just before serving, float scoops of sherbet on top.
Everyone likes this punch because it is not too sweet! The colors are appropriate for spring, but good anytime you need a quick and easy punch for a bunch!

title: chess pies
directions: Cream sugar with butter.
Mix in egg yolks (save whites for meringue).
Add milk, then raisins, then flour.
Pour into tart shells and bake about 15 or 20 minutes at around 375°.
Then top each pie with meringue and put in oven until browned.

title: buttermilk glaze for fresh apple cake
directions: Boil 2 minutes, then pour over cake while still in pan.
Leave 1 hour before turning cake out.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all drained fruit, then stir in marshmallows, coconut and sour cream.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Fill crock-pot with sliced apples.
Drizzle sugar, salt and spices over apples.
Begin cooking on high and then lower heat and cook all day and night or cook until dark colored and thick, stirring occasionally.
Cool and put into containers for freezing or into jars for canning.

title: lime cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix together, then cool.

title: teen special
directions: Brown onion in oleo.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer about 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients in bowl. Make a well and add oil, eggs, water, and pumpkin. Mix till smooth. Grease and flour 3 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Sift both sugar and flour before measuring.
Sift flour four times after measuring.
In a mixing bowl put the egg whites, cream of tartar and salt.
Beat the mixture until it is stiff.
In another bowl beat the egg yolks until they are light in color. Through a sifter add sugar to the egg whites and fold the sugar into the eggs.
Then fold the beaten egg yolks into the sugar and egg white mixture.
Add the flavoring.
Through a sifter add the flour to the other ingredients and fold it into them.
Turn into an ungreased deep tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
When cake is removed from oven, place it, inverted, on a cake cooler until cold.

title: hamburger noodle stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and cook onion until tender.
Stir to separate meat and pour fat off.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased shallow baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir.
Garnish with tomato slices and buttered bread crumbs.
Place in oven for 5 minutes to brown. Yields:
4 1/2 cups.

title: pastel meltaways
directions: In a large bowl, combine butter and powdered sugar.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in cornstarch and flour.
If necessary, chill dough 30 minutes for easier handling.
Shape the dough about the size of a nickel (1/4-inch thick) in a round ball.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes in a 325° oven.
Lightly brown around edges.
Let cool and frost.

title: party punch
directions: Combine juice and water in large nonmetal container. Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Stir in ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 18 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine sugar and 1/2 cup peanut butter until crumbly.
Spread 3/4 of crumbs on bottom of crust.
Mix pudding, milk and 2 tablespoons peanut butter.
Pour over crumbs in shell.
Let set in refrigerator.
Spread Cool Whip and remaining crumbs on top.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Scald sour cream and put into bowl. Add butter, eggs and 1 cup of sugar.
Mix slightly.

title: tahoe brunch
directions: Must prepare 24 hours in advance.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry and pour filling in.
Cover with lattice top.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until done, 35 minutes or a little longer.

title: diabetic sugarless cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, applesauce and raisins. Bring to a boil; stir constantly.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten egg and vanilla.

title: salad dressing
directions: Place onion, sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed and mustard in blender.
Blend thoroughly.
Add oil and blend again.
Great.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to other mixture.
Add carrots and beat well.
Add pecans. Bake in greased and floured pan for about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: potato filling
directions: Saute onion and celery for 3 minutes.
Make filling out of onion, celery, bread, salt and pepper.
Mash the potatoes and add eggs, filling and milk together.
Bake until brown on top, 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with gravy.

title: tuna or chicken noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the chicken or tuna, milk, peas, noodles, soup and salt together.
Pour into a casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes and serve.

title: sticky peaches chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, except chicken, thoroughly.
Coat chicken pieces with this mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet, uncovered, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: company's coming cake
directions: Beat egg whites until just foamy.
Add cream of tartar. Beat until very stiff.
Add
sugar
gradually.
Fold in crackers, vanilla and pecans.
Bake
in lightly greased 7 x 11-inch pan for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a grocery store lime juice (I recommend Neiue and Joe's Key lime juice).
Combine egg yolks and condensed milk; mix well and add lime juice very slowly.
Stir until creamy.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake in oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let chill.
Place in fridge until cold.
Add whipped cream and top with fresh fruit.
Cut and serve.

title: ginger creams
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Stir in baking soda and water.
Sift together and stir in flour, salt, ginger, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon.
Chill dough for 1 hour. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake until set when touched lightly, no imprint remains.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients with a wire whisk to remove large lumps. Add oil and next 3 ingredients, stirring until smooth. Stir in chocolate morsels. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes on wire rack. Remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: california rangers
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well and form into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press lightly with glass.
Bake about 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool before storing.

title: new york specials
directions: Put butter, sugar, marshmallows, cocoa, salt, egg and vanilla in a double boiler until marshmallows are melted.
Remove from stove.
Add graham crackers and coconut.
Press into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix together powdered sugar, melted butter, pudding and cream.
Spread on chocolate base.
Melt 2 squares and 2 teaspoons of butter and drizzle on top.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until good and brown.

title: apricot nectar pound cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Add beaten eggs.
Pour into oblong pan, approximately 9 x 13-inch, and bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and glaze.

title: lemon zucchini cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add beaten egg and lemon peel. Beat until fluffy, on low beater.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in other ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter heavy, large cookie sheet.

title: vanilla wafer balls
directions: Mix well and shape into small balls.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: refrigerator cucumbers
directions: Cut cucumbers into a gallon jar into 1/4-inch slices.
Add onions, then mix ingredients well and pour over cucumbers and onions.
Let set 5 days in refrigerator, then ready to use.
Keep refrigerated.

title: microwave shrimp scampi
directions: Place butter in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High (100%) until melted, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in parsley, lemon juice, garlic and salt.
Add shrimp and toss to coat.
Cover and microwave on High until shrimp is pink, opaque and tender, 3 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes, stirring twice.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: party links
directions: Wrap each Smokie link with bacon and secure with toothpick. Place on cookie sheet and sprinkle with brown sugar over each one. Place in 350° oven.
Bake until bacon looks done.

title: daddy's nachos
directions: Arrange tortilla chips evenly on a microwavable plate.
Top with both grated cheeses; then sprinkle Mrs. Dash evenly.
Top with scallions and tomato (diced black olives are optional). Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Serve with salsa sauce.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in egg. Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: curried pears
directions: Put drained pears in serving dish.
Mix all other ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until it is slightly thickened. Cool slightly.
Pour over pears.
Serves 4 to 6.
(A favorite at the shelter.)

title: spirited coffee lopez
directions: In heatproof pitcher, combine all ingredients, except whipped cream; mix well.
Pour into mugs; top with whipped cream.
Serve immediately.
Makes 5 cups.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans.
Mix shortening and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into pans.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream jello mold
directions: Follow directions on jello package, except omit cold water added to jello (frozen strawberries take place of cold water). After jello is dissolved, add strawberries, crushed pineapple, nuts and bananas and mix together.
Pour half of mixture in mold or baking pan.
Place in freezer for about 45 minutes, then spread sour cream on top and add the rest of the mixture and refrigerate. Cut into pieces.
Use an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan or dish.

title: decadent fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine buttermilk and soda, stirring well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with flour, beginning and ending with flour.
Add 2 bars melted chocolate, chocolate syrup and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in 1 cup mini morsels.
Pour batter into heavily greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Invert cake immediately onto a serving plate and let cool completely.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Stir until mixed well.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken marsala with mushrooms
directions: Dip chicken in flour combined with salt and pepper.
In a large skillet, heat oil and cook chicken over medium-high heat 3 minutes or until browned; remove and set aside.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Cube bread slices and all ingredients together and mix well. Spray loaf pan or 8 x 8 square pan with Pam (or similar pan spray). Pour all ingredients in pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top of bread should be slightly brown.
Cool bread before slicing for easier handling.

title: chicken salad(hot)
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Put in casserole.
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Heat at 425° about 15 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Mix spaghetti sauce and pizza sauce together.
Add ground beef.
Cook 1/2 of the box of spiral macaroni.
Use a casserole dish or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and make layers.
Start with the spirals, then sauce mixture, then cheese and then the pepperoni.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.
Cover while baking.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix well with a fork.
Turn out on floured board and knead gently, about 1/2 minute.
Roll dough about as thin as pie dough. Cut in strips, 1 1/2-inches wide, 3-inches long.
Have broth boiling hot.
Drop one at a time.
Never stir, just shake the kettle gently.
Boil 10 minutes and then lower heat.
Cover.

title: nannie's rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in a greased bowl and cover and leave in a warm place, 1 hour.
Punch dough down and knead on floured board for 10 minutes.
Shape into rolls and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili and egg casserole
directions: Grate cheeses; sprinkle Jack cheese in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle chilies on top.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Beat 2 eggs and flour.
Add half and half; beat again.
Pour all over cheese mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (it should be brown on top).
Great for showers or a lot to feed for breakfast!!

title: lemon-carrot bread 1-loaf
directions: Grind lemon (peel and pulp) with meat chopper or blender.
Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Add oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add carrots and lemon; blend.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to liquid ingredients and mix just to blend.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: savory spaghetti
directions: Brown beef in saucepan.
Drain off the fat.
Add all ingredients except spaghetti.
Cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Serve with meat sauce.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Mix together salt, bread crumbs, grated cheese and 1 cup scalded milk with 1 tablespoon butter, melted in milk.
Add 3 slightly beaten egg yolks.
Beat whites stiff and fold into cheese mixture.
Pour into well-greased 2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: linda's frito boats
directions: Brown meat and drain on paper towel and pour out the fat.
In another skillet, lightly fry the onions and celery.
In a large pot, put the meat and onions, celery and other ingredients (except cheese, chips and garnish items) and let it simmer until tender and seasoned well together.
The longer you cook it, the hotter it seasons together.
This is excellent alone as chili to eat, also. To serve, place your chips in individual soup bowls.
Pour the meat mixture over top, then sprinkle the cheese over top.
Garnish with salsa or sour cream.

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into wax paper-lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg, milk and shortening until flour is dampened.
Spread into a greased 8-inch square pan.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Then add eggs.
Beat until mixed. Stop mixer and add pineapple (juice and all) and then add bread. Put in a 12 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter and butter together. Mix in confectioners sugar until smooth. Form into small balls size of buckeyes (or marbles). Refrigerate balls. Melt slowly chocolate chips and paraffin together in top of double boiler. Using a toothpick, dip buckeyes in chocolate until 2/3 covered. Let dry on wax paper. Makes about 166 or more, depending on size. The golden brown top bulges out over the chocolate skirt and looks like a chocolate dipped nut. Freeze or keep refrigerated.

title: easy spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package; drain.
Mix while hot with cream cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish and put bread crumbs and butter on top, if desired.
Bake in preheated oven for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix in other ingredients.
Make out biscuits.
Keep unused dough in refrigerator.
Keeps several days. Very good!
Makes about 26 biscuits.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Mix together fruit cocktail and dry Jell-O. Add cottage cheese. Mix well and fold in Cool Whip. Chill.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Wash chicken livers and drain.
Lightly saute liver, onion and garlic in butter for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add beer, salt and pepper and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grind or puree in food mill or blender.
Pour into individual crocks.
Refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.
Serve in crocks. Yield: 3 cups.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together in saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla and nuts. Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Spread in a greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar. Cut into bars or squares. Great served with ice cream.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown hash browns in butter.
In separate pan, crumble sausage and cook.
Drain when cooked.
Remove hash browns when done and set aside.
Scramble eggs.
When everything is done, add all ingredients together.
Spoon onto tortillas; sprinkle with cheese and roll.
These are very good served with picante sauce.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix all together
and
freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 small pans.
Cut into squares or slices.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain off fat.
Add chili, refried beans, and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased dish.
Add 1/2 cup of cheese on top.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: yummy salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and add raspberries.
Stir until melted.
Add pineapple; let set.
Add topping.

title: vanilla or lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add boiling water and salt.
Boil, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Add butter and lemon juice (or vanilla).
For generous servings, double the recipe. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
If needed, add more flour to make a dough texture.
Roll out on flour about 1/4-inch thick. Cut into strips and place in skillet with 1/4 cup of hot oil. Brown both sides until it rises.
Take out and top with butter. In separate bowl, mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on top. Delicious for breakfast.

title: banana nut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add bananas and beat well.
Sift all dry ingredients and add alternately with the buttermilk.
Add vanilla and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Great for breakfast or any time.

title: ice box cake
directions: In double boiler melt butter, marshmallows, and Eagle Brand milk.
In large pan mix cracker crumbs and raisins with 1 can of evaporated milk.
Pour melted ingredients over dry ingredients and add nuts.
Mix all ingredients well.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in greased cake pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Crumble over rhubarb in pan.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add all ingredients to the well beaten eggs and mix well. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans (9 x 5-inch) and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and cream first 3 ingredients together.
Chill in a bowl (will still be soft).
Roll in pecans on waxed paper.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash, mash and add sour cream, soup, carrots, onion, salt and pepper.
Put a layer of this mixture in baking dish. Then one of crumbs.
Repeat.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: gram kemp's chop suey
directions: Have meat 1/8-inch thick, cut in 1/4 x 1-inch pieces.
Put in hot oil and simmer slowly until nearly tender.
Drain liquid from sprouts and mix with cornstarch, molasses and sauce.
Add to meat to cook 15 minutes longer.
Saute onions in 1/2 of the butter until glassy; saute celery in remaining butter until nearly tender.
Add this to meat.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add sprouts and cook 3 minutes longer.
If Chinese chestnuts are available, slice thinly and add to the sauce.

title: rum balls
directions: Roll vanilla wafers into crumbs; add sugar and cocoa and add nuts, syrup and rum.
Blend until stiff.
Shape into balls and let stand one hour.
Roll in confectioners sugar and store in tightly closed container for at least three days before using.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop all the vegetables. Brown hamburg and drain. Mix everything together except dressing and chips. Add just before serving (and crush chips).

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain can of cherries and put juice in pot to heat.
If juice is less than 1 cup, add water to make 1 cup. Bring to
a boil. Cut cherries in half and add to juice. Simmer for a couple of minutes. Add hot juice to dry jello in bowl and stir. Add the Coke.
Add the pineapple and juice also.
Mix well and refrigerate until set.

title: cherry slush
directions: Mix together and freeze at least 24 hours.
Scoop frozen mixture into glass and pour ginger ale or 7-Up over it.

title: jerk chicken
directions: In a food processor or blender, combine the green onions, onion, chile pepper, soy sauce, vinegar, vegetable oil, brown sugar, thyme, cloves, nutmeg and allspice. Mix for about 15 seconds. Place the chicken in a medium bowl, and cover with the marinade mixture. Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours, or overnight. Preheat an outdoor grill for high heat, and lightly oil grate. Cook chicken on the prepared grill until no longer pink and juices run clear.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup in saucepan.
Heat, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring until syrup forms a hard ball in cold water (265° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and quickly beat salted egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add syrup to egg whites, beating constantly.
Beat until candy thickens and begins to lose its gloss.
Add flavorings and quickly shape with teaspoon into large pieces and drop onto a greased plate or waxed paper.
Put half a nut on each piece.

title: down south breakfast
directions: Cut tomatoes in halves crosswise; scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Invert to drain.
Place tomatoes in 8-inch casserole dish.
Break an egg into each tomato.
Bake uncovered 15 to 20 minutes at 400° or to desired doneness.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: In Pyrex bowl, combine sugar, butter, salt and syrup.
Cook on High 2 minutes.
Stir with whisk.
Cook on High for 3 minutes, stirring with whisk after each 1 minute interval.
Add vanilla and soda; stir (mixture will foam).

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Make up one package of Jell-O according to directions.
Pour into glass oblong Pyrex dish.
Chill until set.
Spread with sour cream; chill again.
Make up the other Jell-O and let sit until it begins to thicken.
Add the fruit and spread this on top of the first layer.
Chill.
Serve cold.

title: nanna salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine ingredients.
Chill to blend flavors. Stir before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick butter and crumbs together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, eggs, 1 stick butter and vanilla until fluffy.
Spread over crust.
Add well-drained pineapple.
Place sliced bananas, Cool Whip, chopped nuts and cherries over the pineapple.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: okra rice casserole
directions: Mix all well using a fork.
Put in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart buttered casserole dish.
If mixture seems dry, add 1/3 cup of water or tomato juice.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cottage cheese apple pie
directions: Line pie pan with pastry.
Cover with apples.
Beat eggs.
Add cottage cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, cream, salt and lemon rind.
Mix remaining sugar with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over apples, then cover with egg and cheese mixture.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Makes 1 deep dish 9-inch pie.

title: blueberry cheesecake dessert
directions: Follow directions for crust on Jell-O cheesecake box.
Press about 3/4 of mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill in refrigerator about 20 minutes.
Prepare Jell-O batter as directed on box.
When finished, add softened cream cheese to Jell-O mixture and beat with electric mixer until thoroughly mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 of mixture over crust.
Top with blueberries.
Add remaining cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with leftover crumbs.

title: chocolate peanut butter candy
directions: Melt 1 stick butter and remove from heat.
Add vanilla, cocoa and confectioners sugar.
Form into a ball.
Roll out flat, spread on enough peanut butter to cover chocolate.
Roll chocolate back up.
Slice the roll.
Refrigerate.

title: seafood pasta
directions: Saute shallots, garlic, parsley, butter and olive oil until softened.
Add artichokes and sun-dried tomatoes.
Add seafood; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cup of cream; bring to boil.
Serve over pasta.

title: english farmhouse cake
directions: Heat oven to 250° to 300°.
Rub fat into flour with fingertips until it looks like breadcrumbs.
Add all dry ingredients; mix. Slightly beat eggs.
Add eggs to dry ingredients with enough milk to mix a stiff, but sticky dough.
Bake in one pan for 1 1/2 hours, or until cooked.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg whites with electric mixer until foamy; add brown sugar.
Beat mixture until very stiff.
Fold in pecans and drop on greased cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake in 300° preheated oven.
Bake until lightly browned.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger; drain. Add Prego, water and salt. Bring to a boil. In 11 x 7 baking dish layer sauce, uncooked noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers ending with sauce. Garnish with Parmesan cheese. Cover tightly with foil. May also add pepperoni and or mushrooms. Bake at 375° for one hour. Let cool approximately 10 minutes before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles by package directions.
Cook ground beef, garlic and onion in oil; drain excess fat.
Add salt, parsley, pepper, rosemary, water and tomato paste; simmer for 5 minutes.
Blend eggs and cottage cheese.
In 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, put layer of meat sauce, 1/2 noodles, all of cottage cheese and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Save 1/2 cup nuts.
Chill for 1 hour. Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in nuts.
Place on ungreased sheets.
Press thumb in center of each.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Fill thumbprints with jam or jelly.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump ingredients into 13 x 9-inch pan in order.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinade for grilled chicken
directions: Combine marinade ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate a few hours or overnight.
Grill.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: parmesan baked eggplant
directions: Slice unpeeled eggplant crosswise into 1/4-inch thick slices. Sprinkle with salt.
Dip each slice first into beaten egg and then into bread crumbs.
Spray baking sheet with nonstick spray.
Lay eggplant slices flat, not overlapping.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Parmesan.
Dot each slice with butter, if desired, but it really doesn't need it.
Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes or until browned.

title: curried shrimp and ham(4 servings)
directions: In skillet, brown ham and cook onion with curry in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat.
Stir now and then.
Serve.

title: crock-pot venison steak and gravy
directions: Cut venison steak into small pieces.
Roll in flour.
Put into crock-pot; add the 1 cup water.
Cook on high 4 to 6 hours.
Add the mushroom soup to make the gravy.

title: peach french toast(start the night before)
directions: In a saucepan bring brown sugar, butter and water to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes stirring frequently. Pour into a greased 13x9x2 inch baking dish; to with peaches. Arrange bread over peaches.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Melt butter, sugar and milk in large saucepan.
Bring to full boil stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until 234°.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 2 buttered 13 x 9-inch pans.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: salted nut bars
directions: Melt butter, chips and sweetened condensed milk over low heat, then stir in marshmallows.
Spread 1/2 peanuts on bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with first mixture and then sprinkle with remaining peanuts.
Put in refrigerator until set, about 30 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Place all ingredients into large bowl and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Pour cheese sauce over individual servings.

title: grilled corn-on-the-cob
directions: Put 6 ears of corn on individual sheets of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Mix butter, seasoned salt and pepper. Brush over corn. Wrap tightly. Cook on grill for 20 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: grandma's currant pound cake
directions: Rinse currants in hot water; drain and dry on a towel.
Cream butter until fluffy; add sugar and spice and cream thoroughly. Beat egg yolks until thick and creamy; add to butter mixture and blend well.
Add 1/2 of the flour and mix until smooth; add remainder of flour and mix until smooth again.
Mix in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 2 paper lined 9 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Test for doneness by inserting a toothpick in center.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. In another bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in milk, butter, nutmeg and vanilla.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix just until moistened. Fold in blueberries.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Trim meat; brown in oil with onion.
Add barbecue sauce and water, mixing together thoroughly.
Cook for 6 hours on low in crock-pot.
Before serving, shred beef; put back in sauce.
Serve on soft buns or rolls.

title: pancakes
directions: Stir until real smooth and drop with spoon.

title: hungarian chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken parts in large pan. Add the rest of the ingredients except potatoes and noodles.
Add the potatoes when almost done.
Boil egg noodles in separate pan and rinse.
Put noodles in separate dish.
Add to soup individually.

title: mama's irish beef stew
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Dredge meat in seasoned flour; brown in oil.
Add water, tomato sauce, bay leaf and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add vegetables and continue cooking for 20 to 30 minutes.
Thicken with flour for gravy.

title: corn bread(from charlotte lewis' aunt emma)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar and shortening.
Add the egg. Sift the dry ingredients together.
Add the buttermilk alternately with the sifted dry ingredients to the sugar and shortening mixture.
Grease and flour an 8-inch pan.
Pour the batter in the pan.
Bake in the preheated oven for 20 minutes to 1/2 hour, or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: navajo tacos
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients with 1/2 teaspoon salt in a bowl, mixing well.
Knead on floured board until smooth.
Divide into portions and roll out individual fry breads.
Fry in hot, deep oil until brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Remove.
Stir thoroughly; return to oven.
Microwave for 4 more minutes.

title: glazed carrots with herbs
directions: In saucepan of boiling water, cook carrots 5 minutes (tender). Drain in colander; refresh in running cold water.
In a skillet toss the carrots with butter, broth and sugar over moderately high heat until liquid is reduced to glaze.
Stir in parsley and dill. Serves 2.

title: swinging wings
directions: Dip wings in margarine and then in combined mixture of cheese and garlic powder. Place in casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 4.

title: apricot dream salad
directions: Boil pineapple and mix in jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Beat cream cheese and milk.
Add Cool Whip and fold in pineapple.
Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: stephani's mom's potatoes
directions: Mix all but soup together.
Pour soup on top, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: yum-yum gems
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and egg.
Add sour milk.
Stir in sifted ingredients and add raisins and nuts.
Pour in cupcake tins and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
This makes 1 dozen large or 2 dozen small cakes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Stir butter into hot rice. Beat eggs. Add milk, sugar, vanilla, salt and nutmeg. Stir egg mixture into hot rice. Stir in raisins that have been rinsed in hot water. Pour into buttered baking dish. Place in a pan of hot water. Should be 1-inch deep. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Stir gently several times the first 20 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Blend ingredients together in a blender.
Pour mixture into ice cream freezer and add enough regular milk to make a gallon. Freeze.

title: cottage cheese banana splits
directions: Line banana split dishes or salad plates with lettuce.
Cut bananas in half lengthwise.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Place 2 banana halves in each dish.
Combine cottage cheese and coconut; place a scoop in each dish.
Combine pineapple and strawberries; spoon around cottage cheese.
Serve with French salad dressing, if desired.

title: crispy homemade sweet pickles
directions: Slice dill pickles crosswise.
Layer pickles, then sugar, more pickles, more sugar until the container is full or the ingredients have been used.
Extra sugar can be put over all.
Let set in refrigerator a few days.

title: gooey chicken
directions: Flour chicken and place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix soup, water and oleo.
Pour over chicken; bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve hard-cooked eggs, lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash with mayonnaise, mustard, horseradish and relish. Re-fill whites. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken cacciatore(cooking for one or two)
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in hot oil.
Push to one side.
Add onion, green peppers and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, then simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Makes 2 servings.
Good with hot cooked rice, cauliflower and mixed green salad.

title: ground beef and rice stew
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan.
When done, remove from heat. Pour rice and mixed vegetables in a large pot.
Boil both together.
Mix in garlic and onion.
When a low boil is near, mix in ground beef.

title: no-peek casserole
directions: Put all together in casserole dish; cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Might need a little water added before serving.

title: ritz cheese nachos
directions: Place crackers on foil-lined baking sheet; sprinkle evenly with cheese. Top with olives and salsa. Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese begins to melt. Serve immediately.

title: cordon blue casserole(microwave)
directions: Line bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch microwave dish with bread. Top with chicken, ham and broccoli.

Stir onion powder into soup and pour over first mixture. Sprinkle with shredded Swiss cheese. Cover with plastic wrap and vent the plastic wrap to cook. Microwave on 50% power for 15 minutes. Turn 1/4 turn halfway through the cooking time.
Makes 4 servings.

title: leftover soup
directions: Rinse kidney beans in cold water.
Place in pan with all vegetables, stock cube and sufficient water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: welch cakes (picau ar y maen)(with a touch of florida)
directions: Toss together first six ingredients.
Work in butter with pastry blender to resemble coarse bread crumbs.
Add lightly beaten egg and vanilla to dry ingredients along with currants and stir with fork until mixture forms a ball.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface and knead a few times.
Roll to 1/4 inch thickness and cut with round cutter.
If dough is too soft, refrigerate before cutting.
Heat a nonstick skillet to about 320° and bake dough until brown on both sides, about 3 to 5 minutes. Remove cakes to cooling rack and sprinkle with granulated sugar while warm.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Fry sausage.
Drain and crumble.
Place flour in a mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and stir until blended. Stir in sausage.
Knead on a floured board about 10 times.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut with a cutter.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown at 450°.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of 9 x 12-inch loaf pan; add onion soup mix.
Arrange chicken on top.
Mix soups and water together in bowl and pour over rice and chicken.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake 30 minutes at 450°.
Add buttered bread crumbs and bake 20 minutes longer.
Serve with crackers.

title: launee's lasagne
directions: Saute meat, onion and garlic in oil.
Add all other ingredients except cheese and let simmer until sauce is quite thick.
Cook one (10 ounce) package lasagne noodles according to directions; drain. Mix cheeses together and layer noodles, meat sauce and cheeses in oblong baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting it in squares to serve.

title: the chef's gulf coast shrimp creole
directions: Cook and stir onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in butter until onion is tender.
Remove from heat; stir in tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
If mixture is too thick, add a little water.
Stir in shrimp.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 20 minutes or until shrimp is pink and tender.
Serve over rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into shallow pan and bake for 25 minutes in moderate oven.

title: monster cookies(these cookies use no flour)
directions: Cream together sugars, peanut butter and margarine.
Add eggs, vanilla and baking soda.
Mix well.
Stir in oatmeal, chips and M&M's.
Place by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: double chocolate gooey butter cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: sweet and sour chicken or pork
directions: Brown pork or chicken in hot oil.
Add water. Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Combine cornstarch, salt, brown sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce. Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Pour sauce over hot chicken or pork.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Add green pepper, onion and pineapple chunks.
Cook for 5 minutes. Serve over hot fluffy rice and pass extra soy sauce. Serves 7.

title: club chicken
directions: Melt oleo. Add flour, then Pet milk, broth, water and salt. Cook on medium heat until slightly thick. Add pimento, bell pepper and chicken.
Pour in casserole and bake at 400° about 30 minutes. Serve over rice or toast.

title: breakfast potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Peel and slice.

Brown sausages in skillet. Arrange 2/3 of potato slices in bottom of buttered baking dish. Layer eggs over potatoes. Arrange sausage links in center of casserole and place remaining potato slices around edge.
Combine sour cream, milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Pour over casserole. Sprinkle with chives.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cashew turkey salad with honey-lime dressing(or chicken)
directions: Mix meat, onion, oranges, nuts and celery in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, whisk rind, mustard, honey, juice, oil, salt and pepper.
Line a plate with lettuce leaves.
Toss salad ingredients with the dressing; then arrange on lettuce leaves.
(Very pretty for a luncheon, as well as delicious.)

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a large casserole dish. Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Melt 1 stick of butter and pour over crackers.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broken glass cake
directions: Mix each package of jello with 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Pour each in shallow pan and let set overnight.
Mix vanilla wafers, oleo (melted) and 1/2 cup sugar.
Line dish with mix.
Save a small amount to sprinkle on top.
Dissolve gelatine in 2 tablespoons cold water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add to 1/2 cup hot pineapple juice.
Let cool.
When cooled, add to Cool Whip.
Pour into lined dish.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt margarine in Dutch oven.
Salt and pepper to taste the margarine.
Sprinkle flour until thin and pasty.
Add the milk. Cut Velveeta cheese into small pieces and add to mixture.
Add cooked macaroni to cheese mixture and serve.

title: german supper
directions: Cut potatoes into thumb size pieces. Add onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Brown in a small amount of oil for 25 minutes until tender. Add sausage; heat and stir occasionally. Drain kraut and spread on top. DO NOT STIR. Cover and heat.

title: miniature black-bottom cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Combine flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, baking soda, 1/2 teaspoon salt, water, oil and vinegar.
Fill miniature cupcake papers 1/2 full.
Combine cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Drop on each cupcake.
Then sprinkle 6 to 8 chocolate chips on top of each cupcake.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: overnight salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Cover bottom of shallow glass pan.
In layers, sprinkle over lettuce: celery, onion, peppers and cucumber.
Combine sour cream, lemon juice, mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour mixture over salad, but
do not toss.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.
Before serving, crumble bacon over top and decorate with tomato wedges.

title: yum-a-setta
directions: Brown ground beef with salt, pepper, brown sugar and onions. Add tomato soup.
Cook egg noodles and drain. Add cream of chicken soup to noodles.
Stir.
In a casserole dish, layer beef mix, noodle mix with processed cheese between layers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken havana
directions: In small bowl, mix raisins with white wine vinegar. Set aside.

title: chocolate cringles cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Shape into 3/4-inch round balls rolled in 4x sugar. Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes (no longer) in 350° oven.
Don't overbake. Makes 6 dozen.

title: pork chop potato casserole
directions: Fry pork chops with sliced onions.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan or roaster.
Layer potatoes, pork chops (or steak), onion and another layer of potatoes.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over layers.
Cover with foil and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: jessica's unbelievable toffee
directions: Lay a sheet of aluminum foil in cookie sheet pan.
Spray with nonstick cooking spray.
Fill sheet with saltine crackers, side by side.
In saucepan, heat butter and brown sugar on medium heat until foamy.
Pour mixture over crackers and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over crackers.
Wait 2 minutes and spread.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Let harden in freezer.

title: egg custard rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Combine milk, 1/4 cup butter and salt. Stir until butter is melted; cool. Blend in egg custard mix and yeast. Add enough flour to make soft dough.

Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic. Place in buttered bowl and let rise until double in bulk. Turn out on floured board and roll rectangular 20 x 8 inches. In half lengthwise, spread butter on each strip. Fold each strip lengthwise, slightly off center. Gently pull each strip to 24 inches. Cut each strip in 3 inch slices. Seal edges and place on greased cookie sheet. Let rise double. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes until brown.

title: david's delight
directions: Mix these ingredients until crumbly.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan, greased on bottom only.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: creamy potato puff
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and potatoes, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in 1-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: unleavened communion bread
directions: Work flour in.
If it separates when rolled, you need to work in a little more flour.
Roll on aluminum foil.
Wipe countertop with a damp cloth so foil will stick to counter.
Roll thin.
Use tracing wheel to score in little squares.
Punch holes with a toothpick so bread will lay flat.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes.
(Do not brown.)

title: buckeye cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar like pie dough.
Make into small balls and chill.
Melt chocolate and wax in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate with a toothpick, leaving the end uncovered.

title: crusty cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well, at medium speed.
Add cream cheese, beating until light and fluffy.
Alternately add flour and eggs, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.

title: cold bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread into small pieces, cover with milk. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with water.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool.

title: aunt jackie's baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar and flour together, stir in pineapple juice, and beat in the egg.
Either cook in double boiler or in the microwave until the mixture becomes very thick.
Stir occasionally.
While mixture is cooking, layer pineapple, cubed cream cheese and marshmallows.
Pour thickened mixture over the layers.
bake at 350 degrees until bubbly (approx. 30 minutes).
Top with grated cheese and put back into oven until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry eggs with salad oil.
Set aside and cut into small pieces. Mix soy sauce and sugar; set aside.
Saute onion; add meat, onions and rice.
Stir until hot.
Add egg and stir.
Add soy sauce mixture and stir.

title: lemon meringue mousse
directions: This recipe is a restaurant sized portion.
Can be cut in half.

title: spanakopeta
directions: Cook onions, scallions and parsley with olive oil.
Add spices and cook on low heat, stirring constantly.
In a bowl crumble cheese and add milk and eggs.
Pour over chopped spinach and mix. Add cooled herbs and mix well.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream 3 Tbsp. sugar with butter.
Add crushed pretzels, mix well.
Then press into a 9x14 inch glass pan.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely. Combine cream cheese and 1 c. sugar until smooth.
Fold in cool whip.
Spread over cooled pretzel crust.
Chill.
Dissolve gelatin in 2 c. boiling water.
Then add 1/2 c. cold water.
Stir in strawberries.
Chill until partly set. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Return to refrigerator and chill until firm.

title: crunchy fruit cobbler(used with reindeer treats)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice unpeeled fruit into small chunks. Put 2 cups "Reindeer Treats" into a bowl.
Add chopped fruit and 1 cup honey.
Stir until honey coats the ingredients.
Use half of the softened butter to coat the inside of the baking dish, cover bottom and sides completely.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Cut remaining butter into chunks (small) and sprinkle on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm by itself or with milk or ice cream.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat eggs; add vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: dressing
directions: I cook celery and onion prior.
Mix and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° until browned slightly.

title: sausage balls
directions: In a large bowl, mix the pork, bread crumbs, onion, egg and salt.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Cook meatballs until well browned.
Remove meatballs and put in bowl as they brown.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings from skillet.
Into remaining drippings, stir in flour, pepper and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk and 1 cup water.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens slightly, stirring constantly.
Return meatballs to skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add in your crust. Bake at 300°.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together until they are thoroughly blended.
Enough for 6-quart freezer.

title: peach tote dandy
directions: Grease 8-inch square baking pan with 2 tablespoons butter or oleo.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Drain peaches and arrange on top of brown sugar.
Stir biscuit mix, sour cream, 2 tablespoons melted butter or oleo, sugar, allspice, unbeaten egg, orange peel and nuts just until blended.
Then beat well, about 30 seconds. Spread mixture evenly over peaches and bake in hot oven (400°) for 25 minutes or until tests done.
Cool 5 minutes; turn out onto rack.
Store in metal cake tin.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lace cookies
directions: Grind almonds in blender.
Set aside.
Melt butter; add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add nuts, flour and salt.
Cook and stir about one minute.
Remove from heat and add milk.
Stir in. Drop from soup spoon on buttered cookie sheet (Teflon is best). Flatten with back of spoon or fingers.
Do only 3 or 4 at a time (leave room for spreading).
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes or until light brown.
Remove from oven.
Count to 10.
