Lift off; loosen edges first, then shape over bottom of glass and cool.
If hardens too much, put in oven and warm up.

title: rice pudding
directions: Add cooked rice, half and half or milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes until all milk is absorbed.
Add milk as needed to give pudding creamy consistency.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix.
Spread evenly in 12 x 18-inch glass dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in the order listed.

title: midget date loaves
directions: Pour the water over the dates and shortening.
Cool to room temperature. Add the orange peel and orange juice.
Stir in the egg.
Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Add to mixture. Stir just until mixed. Stir in the walnuts. Turn into 4 greased 4 1/2 x 2 3/4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Or bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from pans. Cool. Wrap and store overnight.

title: sourdough sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon or frost.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Let first 3 ingredients boil.
Drop from spoon the mixture of sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and egg into fruit.

title: coconut icing
directions: Place in bowl and mix thoroughly after coconut has thawed. Makes enough for 3 layer cake, top and sides.

title: lemon squares
directions: Crust:
Mix flour and butter.
Press into pan, then press chopped walnuts into dough.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: french fries
directions: Get a potato at the store, then you get milk and pickles.
Cut the potatoes up.
Eat with chicken nuggets.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add eggs, water, oil, vanilla and puddings.
Stir well.
Pour 1/2 batter in 9 x 12-inch pan. Sprinkle part of cinnamon mixture on batter.
Add rest of batter and the remaining cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: one pot chicken dinner
directions: Brown chicken in skillet and salt.
Remove and put in a large casserole dish. Add potatoes, carrots and soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat beef cubes with this mixture.
Brown in oil.
Add water, tomato sauce and seasonings. Add frozen vegetables.
Cook over low heat 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to a boil. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter. Mix in 2 cups of cornflakes. Drop on foil and let cool.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill before using.
Will store well for up to a week in tightly covered container.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Spray bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan with Pam.
Spread hash brown potatoes over bottom of pan.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Put rhubarb in 9 x 13 pan. Combine sugar, cornstarch and water in saucepan. Cook until thick and clear. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour over rhubarb. Mix together flour, oatmeal, butter, brown sugar and cinnamon. Crumble over rhubarb and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and place in a greased 8 x 12-inch dish.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
While baking, prepare egg, butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat with mixer.
Pour over baked, cooled graham crackers.
Let set in refrigerator while preparing whipping cream, Dream Whip or topping mix.
Add pineapple, mix and pour over dessert.
Shave chocolate bar over top and chill several hours or overnight.

title: mediterranean casserole
directions: Arrange vegetables in layers in casserole.
Sprinkle with herbs and oil. Cover and microwave until tender, about 12 minutes, stirring several times. Add salt and pepper.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse sauerkraut with cold water.
Drain well.
Combine with pepper, onion, celery and celery seed in medium bowl.
Heat sugar with water, oil and vinegar until dissolved.
Pour over sauerkraut mixture.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: potato breakfast casserole
directions: Cover hash browns with hot water; let stand 10 minutes. Drain well.
Beat eggs; add potatoes and remaining ingredients except bacon and paprika.
Pour mixture into a buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with bacon and paprika.
Cover dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: yam souffle
directions: Drain and mash yams.
Mix ingredients well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered dish.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add milk, sugar, oil and salt.
Sift and gradually add the flour and soda to the yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Roll out and shape into rolls. Let rise until double in size, about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° or 425° until rolls are brown
on top.

title: raisin caramels
directions: Place raisins in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine 3/4 cup butter or margarine and 1 cup brown sugar in saucepan; cook and stir to hard ball stage (254°).
Pour over raisins.
Top with 1/2 cup semi-sweet chocolate pieces, spreading as they melt.
Chill until firm; cut in pieces.

title: crab and pea salad
directions: In a bowl, combine peas, crab and bacon.
Combine mayonnaise and onion powder; fold into crab mixture.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: squash puppies
directions: Boil squash until tender and drain.
Mash squash; drain again. Mix the remaining ingredients with squash and shape or drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook until brown.

title: polynesian honey dip
directions: Place sour cream in blender; mix a few seconds until smooth. Gradually add brown sugar, mixing to blend.
Add honey and brandy; mix a few more seconds to blend.
Chill.
Serve as a dip with bite-size cubes of fresh coconut.

title: barbecued baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the bacon.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Place the raw bacon slices on top.
Cover; bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: chicken bisque
directions: Combine chicken stock, chicken, green pepper and pimentos. Simmer for 30 minutes and season to taste (salt and pepper).
Melt butter over low heat and add flour a little at a time.
When flour is lightly browned, add a few tablespoons of hot soup and blend into smooth paste.
Stir into simmering soup and continue stirring until it thickens.
Garnish with croutons.
Yield:
8 portions. Serve with cheese bread and tossed salad.

title: baked salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; press into loaf shape.
Place in open baking pan lined with heavily greased aluminum foil.
Bake 40 minutes at 370°.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients and pour in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl and mix.
Add oil, vinegar, vanilla and water; beat well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Place sugar, water and butter in pan over high heat.
Boil 2 minutes or to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add pecans and vanilla.
Beat until mixture becomes creamy and begins to sugar on the side of the pan.
Then drop from spoon onto wax paper.

title: fruited cream dessert
directions: Dissolve package of Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 pint vanilla ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until ice cream is melted.
Add about 2/3 cup diced, drained fruit.
Chill until set, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with 1 cup diced fruit.
Serves 6.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in salted water.
Add milk to eggs to measure 1 cup liquid.
Mix with grits.
Add cheese and margarine.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 325° about 30 minutes.
Top with 1/2 cup shredded sharp cheese.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Mix well and bake for 8 minutes in a 400° oven.
Cool.

title: sausage and rice dish
directions: Brown sausage; drain off fat.
Add vegetables; simmer.
In separate pan, boil water.
Add rice and soup mix; simmer for 10 minutes.
Mix sausage and vegetables with rice and soup in casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, covered.

title: better than . . . cake
directions: Mix grated chocolate and chocolate chips with cake mix.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Make in a Bundt or tube pan at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean, or 45 to 50 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Pour half the batter into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with half of the grated cheese.
Pour remaining batter and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: homemade broccoli soup
directions: In a heavy pot, heat butter and flour; stir until smooth.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Heat thoroughly over medium heat.
Add spices, broccoli and milk to desired thickness.
Cook over medium heat, covered, until broccoli is done.
Add cheese and half and half.
Bring to a boil to melt cheese.
Turn off, serve immediately.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat; stir until blended. Remove from heat.
Gradually blend in milk.
Mix cornstarch, salt and sugar; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Mix coconut and pecans; sprinkle over filling.

title: cashew crunch
directions: Cook and stir sugar and butter until creamy.
Add cashews. Cook and stir until brown and creamy.
Pour onto wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: too easy muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Batter will be lumpy.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and shortening; add eggs and apples.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix with sugar mixture.
Add pecans.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into greased 10 x 6 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: christmas candy
directions: In a double boiler or saucepan, slowly melt the almond bark over low heat.
Pre-measure all other ingredients and mix in a large bowl.
When all of the blocks have melted to a liquid consistency, remove from heat.
With a wooden spoon, stir in the ingredients combined in the large bowl.
Stir lightly, but quickly until every piece is coated in the white almond bark.
Drop spoonfuls of candy mixture onto wax paper.
Allow to dry completely and enjoy!

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In small bowl combine 2 Tbsp. brown sugar, corn syrup, pecans and 1 Tbsp. of the margarine. Spoon about 2 tsp. of the mixture into each of 9 muffin pans cups. Unroll entire crescent roll dough; pinch seams together to form 1 rectangle. Combine remaining 1 Tbsp. brown sugar and the cinnamon. Spread dough with remaining 1 Tbsp. margarine; sprinkle with cinnamon mixture. Roll up from short end. Cut into 9 slices. Place 1 slice in each prepared muffin cup. Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately invert pan onto tray; cool 10 minutes.

title: hot cinnamon tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea.
Brew 4 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add sugar.
Squeeze juice from lemons and oranges and stir into tea.
Add cinnamon and cloves; heat over low heat (about 200°).
Garnish each serving with a slice of lemon speared with a clove.
Serves 8.

title: pizza hot dogs
directions: Split hot dog buns and wieners lengthwise.
Place layer of cheese on buns.
Add wiener slices to each bun.
Top with pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place on broiler pan. Broil until brown and bubbly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, potatoes and onion until tender.
Mix with cream of chicken and margarine.
Pour stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage hash brown casserole
directions: Mix everything but the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Take out of oven and sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: layered pizza dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a greased 9-inch pie plate or 1 to 1 1/2-quart baking dish, layer all ingredients in order given. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until dip is hot and cheese is melted. Serve warm with bagel crisps, bagel chips or crackers.

title: texas triple dip
directions: Layer equal amounts of guacamole, dairy sour cream and Pace picante sauce in a clear glass bowl.
Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.
Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On a large, flat oven pan, split English muffins and lay cut side up.
Spoon 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons of tomato sauce on each muffin.
Sprinkle 1 to 2 dashes oregano and 1 to 2 dashes garlic powder on each one.
Sprinkle 1 to 2 dashes of Parmesan cheese on each muffin and top with Mozzarella cheese as desired.

You may add other things, if desired, like onions, peppers, mushrooms and vegetarian pepperoni, sliced or chopped. Cook at 350° for 10 minutes until cheese is lightly browned; with vegetables, etc., it will take a little longer.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add taco seasoning.
Mix tomato sauce and chili beans.
Grate cheese and crush Doritos.
Place layer of meat mixture, layer of cheese and then layer of Doritos. Repeat until gone.
Place whole or crushed Doritos on top.
Cook in oven at 350° until cheese is melted on top of casserole.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased skillet.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture; add other half of batter.
Bake at 400° until done (about 1 hour).

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sugar, juice and cornstarch together until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add butter; pour over potatoes in casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 4.

title: 15 minute chicken and rice dinner
directions: In medium skillet over med-high heat, heat oil. Add chicken and cook 8 minutes or until browned. Set chicken aside. Pour off fat. Add soup, water, paprika and pepper. Heat to boil. Stir in rice and broccoli. Place chicken on rice mixture. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until done. Pour glaze over warm loaves.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage in wedges and place in bottom of casserole dish. Brown meat and onion, then add rice, soup, chili beans, tomatoes and water to hamburger.
Heat together and pour over cabbage. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring to boil the first three ingredients.
Add peanuts and food coloring.
Cook to soft ball stage (245°).
Remove from heat and add butter.
Mix until you can't stir.
Drop onto wax paper.

title: breakfast egg and cheese bake
directions: Brown sausage links and drain.
Cut up in pieces.
In large bowl, mix together eggs, milk, Cheddar cheese and sausage.
Pour over bread in glass pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour in 325° oven.
Do not overbake.

title: chinese ribs
directions: Sprinkle ribs with ginger and garlic powder.
Mix together soy sauce and honey.
Brush mixture on ribs.
Line a baking pan with foil.
Place ribs in pan and bake at 350° for 2 hours, basting frequently and turning after the first hour.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut bacon into little pieces and fry in pan until brown. Drain well.
Clean and cut up broccoli and cauliflower.
Place all ingredients in a large bowl and mix together 2 hours before serving.
If you want, you can make the night before.
Stir well before serving.

title: linzer hearts
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup of sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix well.

title: dolly's easy pie
directions: Empty filling into 8 or 9-inch square pan and sprinkle with cinnamon to taste.
Beat one egg slightly and add vanilla extract. In another bowl mix next 3 ingredients.
Add egg and mix until crumbly.
Distribute evenly over pie filling.
Pour margarine over top and bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown and done.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight container. To serve, mix
about
1/4 cup mix with hot water or add mix to taste.

title: bologna
directions: Mix this and grind
again.
Work
in
quarts
water. Pack in jars.
Process quarts
at
10 pound pressure for 1 1/2 hours or in hot water bath for 3 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple.
Add Cool Whip, miniature marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well and chill overnight before serving.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir in condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cool and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Arrange 2 bananas on bottom of cooked pie shell.
Pour filling over bananas.
Cover.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Spread top with whipped cream.
Garnish with remaining banana slices. Refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind together cranberries and orange.
Add sugar.
Let stand 1 hour, then combine lemon jello with the hot water.
Let stand 1 hour.
Combine with crushed pineapple.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.

title: crustless spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven; spread evenly over bottom of pan (and halfway up sides). Beat eggs; add milk, flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well. Stir in spinach, cheese and onions.
Spoon into buttered baking pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.
(Quiche will be relatively flat and quite firm in texture.)

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all but last ingredient and put into cooking dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and spread on top. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: egg and macaroni toss
directions: Mix all ingredients in	a
large
bowl; toss and chill. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.

title: beef-a-roni
directions: Cook macaroni until done. Brown beef with onions and peppers; drain. Add sauce to beef. Add macaroni to sauce mixture. Pour in oblong pan top with cheese. Bake at 325° until cheese starts to brown, 20 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve with vegetables.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: In large saucepan melt margarine.
Add onion, garlic and celery.
Cook until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add squash, chicken broth, marjoram, bay leaf and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until squash is tender.
Remove bay leaf and cool soup for 5 minutes.
Whirl soup in blender or food processor for 30 seconds.
Return soup to saucepan.
Add buttermilk, reheat.
Do not boil, or it will curdle.
Ladle into cups.

title: gambas al ajillo(garlic shrimp)
directions: Wash shrimp well and allow to drain.
Peel garlic cloves and combine with salt in a mortar and pound with pestle until creamy. Combine shrimp, garlic mixture, parsley and pepper.
Place mixture in glass container, cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or until ready to cook.

title: little date nut loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 5 miniature loaf pans (4 1/2 x 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches).
Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir just until blended.
Divide batter among prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter until light.
Add and beat well 6 whole eggs. Alternate 4 cups cake flour, 3/4 c. sweet milk and 1/2 tsp. vanilla almond flavor.
After all ingredients are combined, beat at high speed for 1 minute.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 2 hours at 300°.
Cool in pan, do not invert Yields 20 pieces.
Do not open oven during cooking.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix well in blender.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Grease another bowl.
Put dough in greased bowl and turn over once to grease all sides.
Cover lightly with foil and stand overnight.
If you do not have a warm place, it may take up to 24 hours.
After raising to top of bowl, punch down.
Divide into 3 loaves.
Knead each part on floured surface 8-10 times.
Put in greased loaf pan. Brush with butter.
Let rise 4-8 hours or double in size.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Store in tightly covered jar in cool, dry place.
To use, place 3 tablespoons of mix in cup.
Stir in a small amount of boiling water to dissolve powder, then fill cup.
Stir well and serve with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: harvest time dessert
directions: Combine apples and sugar and let stand.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir in apples and sugar mixture; add nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: black-eyed pea shrimp gumbo
directions: In a 6-quart Dutch oven, combine water, tomatoes, hot pepper sauce, Cajun seasoning, garlic and onion.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in rice and okra. Simmer, covered, an additional 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and peas; cook until heated through.
Makes eight 1 1/4-cup servings.

title: fruit cups
directions: Drain some juice to mix with the pudding.
Pour over fruit. Good for several days.

title: old virginia wassail
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a simmer.
Strain and serve hot.
Also delicious when cold.

title: imitation crab salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve.
Best if cool.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Blend in sugar, flour, margarine and vanilla.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour into shell. Bake 50 minutes or until lightly golden brown and firm on top (325°).

title: alcoholic cocktails
directions: Blend the ice and put it in the glass.
Mix well all the ingredients in a shaker and then pour the mixture in the glass with the ice.
Decorate your cocktail with a maraschino cherry.

title: play dough
directions: Bring water, salt and food coloring to a boil and boil until salt is dissolved.
Add oil, alum and flour; stir until dough is a ball, then knead in flour until play dough consistency.
Store in Ziploc bag.
Have fun!

title: old settler's baked beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and bacon.
Add onion, brown sugar, catsup, barbecue sauce, salt, pepper and molasses.
Mix well.
Add the beans.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour 1/2 the mixture into 12-inch greased pan or skillet.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Pour on remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: russian dressing(quick)
directions: Mix very well and pour over lettuce wedges.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Put broccoli in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken on top.
Mix soup with mayonnaise and pour over chicken. Sprinkle mushrooms, then cheese over all.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over all, then drizzle melted butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or a little longer uncovered.

title: coconut pies
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Put in 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: better 'n fried chicken
directions: Remove skin and all visible fat from chicken.
Put all ingredients in a plastic bag with chicken pieces and shake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: afterschool carrot cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in egg and lemon extract. Stir in carrots and raisins, then sifted dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: potato wedges
directions: Spread potatoes in a single layer on cookie sheet.
Coat with cooking spray and sprinkle with seasonings.
Bake in a 450° oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve as a snack.

title: chicken waikiki
directions: Brown chicken in oil and drain. Mix 1/4 cup pineapple liquid with tomato sauce and vinegar. Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and cornstarch.
Simmer until clear and thick.
Add pineapple chunks. Stir constantly.
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: old fashion chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring continually.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla; beat until you can spread on cake.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir butter into hot spaghetti. Stir in Romano and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti crust.

title: strawberry delight cake
directions: Crumble cake into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix pudding and ice cream and pour over cake.
Put in refrigerator and let set.
Mix Jell-O as directed on box and mix with strawberries. Add to cake mixture and place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: cheese-potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and onions.
Place in saucepan and add enough water to completely cover by 1/2-inch.
Bring to a slow boil and cook until done.
Add butter and seasonings.
If soup is thin, you can add a small amount of instant potatoes.
When all is blended, add cheese, which has been cut in small pieces.

title: fried fruit pies
directions: Cut Crisco into flour, sugar and salt.
Break eggs into 2-cup measuring cup.
Beat slightly with fork and add enough water to make 2 cups liquid.
Mix into flour mixture and form into ball. Roll out on lightly floured board, real thin. Cut around a saucer or etc.
Place ample amount of fruit on dough round.
Moisten edges, fold over and seal with fork.
Prick pie with fork 2 to 3 times to prevent air.
Heat Crisco in skillet over medium heat and fry until golden brown, turning only once.
Use dried apples or peaches, cooked and sweetened.

title: mushroom and cheese omelette
directions: Heat half the butter in a frying pan and add mushrooms and garlic.
Cook over moderate heat 5 minutes or until mushrooms begin to soften.
Add thyme, rosemary and white wine and continue to saute another 5 minutes or until liquid evaporates.
Season to taste with salt and freshly ground pepper.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: easy barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving size pieces; put in large pot and cover with water.
Salt lightly and boil until almost fork-tender. Remove from pot; place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix Coke and barbecue together; pour over ribs.
Cover in foil.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Place butter and brown sugar in saucepan; heat and stir to boiling.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk; cool.
Stir in powdered sugar, a half cup at a time.
If thin, add more powdered sugar.
This is good on applesauce spice cake.

title: chicken burritos
directions: Boil chicken breast until done. Drain and shred chicken. In pot/saucepan, add Ro-Tel to chicken and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sauce dip for chicken fingers
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with chicken fingers.

title: biscuit mix(make your own)
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter in large mixing bowl. Mix well with kitchen fork.
Work butter into mixture with fingers until the consistency of fine corn meal.
Store in airtight container in cool place.
Makes 11 cups of mix; use same as Bisquick.

title: cold rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions and cool.
Add onions, pepper and olives to rice.
Drain artichokes and save juice. Combine juice and curry powder with mayonnaise.
Pour over rice, sliced artichokes and shrimp.
Chill.
Better done day before.

title: gala crab salad
directions: In a bowl combine rice, crab, salad dressing, green pepper, onion and celery.
Pack into an oiled 6-cup mold.
Chill at least 6 hours or overnight.
Unmold onto a bed of leaf lettuce.
Garnish with parsley and lemon if desired.
Yields 4 to 6 main dish or 12 to 14 side dish servings.

title: veal casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and bake at 300° until tender.

title: mama's baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients, adding pork and beans last.
Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes, stirring so mixture will not scorch. Pour into a baking dish and bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 additional minutes.
For added flavor, put 1 inch strips of bacon on top before baking.

title: saucy little meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients real good.
Roll into little round balls.
Put into square pan; press down a little.
Pour the sauce over the top.

title: crescent cream cheese squares
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, spread 1 package of crescent rolls on bottom of pan.
Cream sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Spread on top of rolls.
Top cream cheese mixture with package of rolls. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 400° for 30 minutes in a greased pan.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Spread in 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Spread melted chocolate chips over mixture. Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli; drain.
Chop with fork and put in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Combine cheese and mushroom soup over low heat in saucepan until cheese is completely melted.
Pour over cooked broccoli.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle onions over and put back in oven until lightly browned.

title: spinach quiche-gourmet
directions: Bake pie shell (prick all over with fork) in 350° oven until set but not brown.
While pastry bakes, prepare spinach according to package directions.
Empty into deep bowl; allow to cool slightly.
Stir in onions, seasonings, eggs and cream.
Pour into hot pie shell.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean, 40 minutes.
May be further browned under broiler a few minutes, if desired.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Spread over rhubarb.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Spread over top layer. Garnish with graham crackers (crushed).
Refrigerate.

title: cajun oyster stew
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until al dente.
Add mushrooms.
Cook 1 minute over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk gradually until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add oysters, potato soup, pimentos and Tabasco. Heat until oysters curl, about 10 minutes.

title: cabbage and potato soup
directions: Use as much as you want of first 5 ingredients.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti according to package directions.
Heat olive oil; add onion and cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce, garlic, oregano, basil and pepper.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for 10 minutes. Place ziti in baking pan and add sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: a recipe for a mother
directions: Mix all ingredients gently.

title: tuna vegetable salad
directions: Bring water, peas, carrot, onion, salt and pepper to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Cover and chill.
Gently stir in tuna, pickle, mayonnaise and milk just before serving.
Serve on crisp salad greens.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salsa ole
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer in saucepan about 20 minutes on low heat.

title: cherry pastry
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread 3/4 of thick batter in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with cherry or other filling. Drop remaining batter by spoonfuls on filling.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, eggs, butter, Bisquick and vanilla in bowl; mix on low speed for 3 minutes with mixer.
Pour into desired pan; let stand for 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cut or string beef in pan.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, mustard, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir well and simmer over medium heat approximately 30 minutes.

title: holiday peppermint fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 8-inch pan with foil.
Over low heat in saucepan, melt condensed milk with butter.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla chips and white chocolate squares (broken up).
Add peppermint; stir until all chocolate is melted.
Pour into pan.
Dot the top with red and green coloring.
Drag knife through it to give marbled effect.
Refrigerate 8 hours.
Cut into squares after turning out onto cutting board.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk in heavy (2 1/2 to 3-quart) saucepan.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch square of 13 x 9-inch baking pan or line pan with aluminum foil.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: applesauce, chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix soda and applesauce together.
Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add applesauce mixture.
Add flour and spices that have been sifted together.
Add nuts and chips.
Drop on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: sweet italian sausage and bow ties
directions: Parcook sausage in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.
Deskin and slice thin; set aside.
Cook bow ties; reserve 1 cup liquid before draining.
Cook onion in olive oil until clear.
Add sausage; cook thoroughly.
Add 1 tablespoon seasoning and peppers.
Add bow ties, liquid and seasoning.
Toss until blended.
Serve topped with Parmesan cheese.

title: nacho dip
directions: In a baking dish, mix the refried beans with a half package of taco seasoning mix.
Spread sour cream on top.
Chop olives and chilies and lay them on top of the sour cream.
Place sliced cheese on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: apricot pineapple mold
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Bring to a boil; set to cool.
When mixture is starting to set, add 2 packages beaten Dream Whip.
Fold into Jell-O.
Mold.

title: mexican fruit bowl dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve in cut glass bowl.
Omit Cointreau if you wish.
Delightful after a heavy meal.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Mix the meat, onion, eggs, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Add rice.
Precook cabbage leaves for 3 minutes in small amount of boiling water; drain.
Spoon meat mixture into cabbage leaves.
Roll cabbage leaves around meat mixture; secure with toothpicks.
Put in baking pan with tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (or until done).

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Heat in heavy medium saucepan until boiling.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese.
Stir; heat at medium-low temperature until cheese is smooth and creamy.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix eggs, butter, flour and sugar together, then add chips and nuts. Pour into pie crust and bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Cream the sugar, eggs, oil and salt.
Add zucchini and all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: avocado tossed salad
directions: Prepare lettuce into bite size pieces (about 4 cups).
Cut avocado lengthwise in half.
Remove pit, peel and slice crosswise into bowl.
Pour salad dressing over lettuce and toss.
Divide mixture among 5 individual salad bowl servings.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cakes according to directions on cake mix.
Let cool. In a large, deep pan or on a plate, you start by taking 1/2 the Kahlua to the first box of cake mix by setting the first layer in a pan or plate.
Pour 1/4 cup of Kahlua over 1 layer of cake. Cover the layer with 1/2 of the first container of Cool Whip. Crush the Skor bars and sprinkle some over the layer.
Repeat layers until all done with all four layers.

title: corn salad
directions: Use amount of celery, pepper and onion as desired.
Heat sugar, vinegar and oil.
Let cool and pour over vegetables. Refrigerate.

title: bacon-chestnut wraps
directions: Place half of bacon on a microwave roasting rack.
Cover with paper towels (I put mine in the oven on a bread pan because I save the bacon grease).
Cook on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, or until bacon is slightly brown, not completely cooked.
Repeat with remaining bacon slices.
Wrap each piece of bacon around a water chestnut and a piece of green pepper; secure with a toothpick. Place in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour over wrapped water chestnuts. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Microwave at High for 6 to 9 minutes or until done.
